title: stir-in-the-pan-cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour oil in 9 x 13 pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered in oil. Pour cake mix, eggs, water and pudding mix into pan. Stir until well blended. Scrape sides and spread evenly. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: banana-blueberry bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place liners in 12 (1/2 cup) muffin cups or lightly grease.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix well in dishpan and drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients.
Then add the next 5 ingredients to this mixture and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Pack in jars while mixture is hot and seal.

title: christmas cutout cookies
directions: Blend together the sugar, butter and eggs.
Add salt, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Add flour alternately with milk. Roll, cut and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Ice when cool.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: quick bread
directions: Bake in greased loaf pan about 45 minutes at 375°.

title: ranch chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and pineapple.
Mix salad dressing mix with mayonnaise and 1/4 cup pineapple juice.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine in a sauce pan sugar, cocoa and butter.
Boil for two minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats, coconut and peanut butter.
Mix well.	Working quickly drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Let stand 10-15 minutes until completely cooled.

title: fresh tomato bruschetta
directions: Cut tomatoes in half horizontally and squeeze out seeds.
Cut tomato into very small dice.
Place in a colander and drain 30 minutes. Transfer tomatoes into a bowl and add next 7 ingredients.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar,
cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until soft ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: cocoa krispies ice cream balls
directions: Combine Cocoa Krispies and coconut in shallow pan or dish; set aside.
Shape ice cream into 8 balls.
Roll quickly into Cocoa Krispies mixture until coated.
Freeze until firm.
Serve plain or with desired sauce.

title: microwave asparagus clam chowder
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in deep casserole for 30 seconds in the microwave. Add onion and cook 2 1/2 minutes or until limp. Stir in the potato and 1 cup of the water. Drain the clam broth into casserole (reserving clams).
Cover and cook 6 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; then add sour cream, vanilla, flour, soda and baking powder.

title: watercress soup
directions: In kettle saute leeks in butter until golden brown.
Wash watercress; dry and chop.
Add to leeks.
Add parsley, garlic and chicken broth.
Bring soup to boil; cook about 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from heat and cool.
Place mixture into blender and mix. Do not overmix.
Add milk, cream, salt and pepper to taste.
This can be served both cold or hot.
Serve with garlic toast and with your favorite dishes.

title: oat-buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix oatmeal and buttermilk in a small covered bowl. Refrigerate overnight.
Add beaten egg and sifted dry ingredients in morning.
Mix all.
Add vegetable oil and more liquid if needed.
Bake on lightly greased griddle.
Makes about 12 pancakes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Place 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons of crushed vanilla wafers in each tart pan liner.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Fill with mixture almost to top of liner.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and top with cherry, apple or strawberry pie filling.
Chill.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and add onions.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, water, taco seasoning, hot pepper sauce and refried beans.
(Beans make it thick and pasty.
If too thick, add more water but don't get it runny.)
Let mixture cool.
Line bottom of pan with meat mixture, then layer sour cream, lettuce and cheese on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tropical treats
directions: Sprinkle chopped, mixed dried fruit in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Using the original Rice Krispies Treats recipe, gently press cereal mixture into pan on the top of mixed fruit.
Put in freezer for 30 minutes.
Invert pan and cut into squares.
Yields 24.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Add last 3 ingredients.

title: velveeta cheese spread
directions: Place butter, onion and peppers into double boiler.
Cook until soft.
Add cheese and melt.
Add ketchup.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately to creamed mixture with applesauce.
Turn batter into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Spoon onto tortillas.
Roll to enclose filling.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tomato raspberry jam
directions: Boil tomatoes, sugar and lemon juice for 20 minutes.
Shut off heat and stir in gelatin.
Let stand for 5 minutes to dissolve. Pour into containers and freeze.
Delicious if you like raspberry jam.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Knead 12 to 15 minutes until smooth and satiny.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise until double in bulk, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Push down, knead briefly, let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 round loaves.
Place loaves on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until double in bulk. Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes until brown and loaves sound hollow.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots and onions.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix
and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: penuche
directions: Boil sugar and milk, stirring to prevent scorching.
Cook to soft ball stage (235° to 240°).
Remove from heat; let cool after adding butter or margarine.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts.
Pour quickly into greased pan.
Makes 12 (1-inch) squares.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding, milk and orange juice together and beat with rotary beater 1 to 2 minutes.
Add yogurt or sour cream, drain all fruit and add.
Can be topped with cherries if desired.

title: diabetic corn pudding(calories: 186)
directions: Beat the egg and mix with the corn, pepper and salt.
Pour the mixture into an individual baking dish.
Place the butter on top of the mixture.
Place the baking dish in a pan of water and bake in a moderate oven for about 20 minutes.
When an inserted silver knife comes out without the mixture adhering, remove from the oven.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg, vanilla, flour and milk.
When mixed well, divide in half.
Add cocoa to 1 part.
Roll out chocolate mixture, then roll out vanilla dough.
Lay on top of chocolate; roll up in long roll.
You make 3 rolls.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Slice and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar and corn meal.
Mix well in center and add remaining ingredients; stir briskly.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together and top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated well.

title: sue's pesto sauce
directions: Process in food processor.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted oleo and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°, covered, for about an hour or until tender.
Baste every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: almond chocolate sticks(a new england recipe)
directions: Cream the cheese with butter until soft and blended. Beat in sugar and vanilla. Stir flour and baking powder into cheese mixture. Spread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 min. or until firm and lightly browned on edges. Sprinkle chocolate over top and let stand to melt. Spread until evenly coated. Sprinkle with almonds. Cool then cut lengthwise into 1 inch strips. Cut across to get 4 inch lengths. Yield 27 sticks.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Turn batter into greased and lightly floured 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done. Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out onto rack and cool completely.
If desired, dust with confectioners sugar before serving.
Makes 16 servings.

title: jamie's easy caramel corn
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar, white syrup and cream of tartar to boil in heavy pan.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring.
Pour over popcorn, stirring as you pour.
Make into balls or eat as is.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Mix sugar, gelatine, milk, vanilla and yolks together in a double boiler and cook (let come to a boil).
Cool.
Add egg whites; beat light and add 1/2 pint of whipped cream and small can of crushed pineapple that has been drained.
You can use pineapple juice to make part of the cup of milk.
Sprinkle some of the crushed graham crackers on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour the cooked mixture on the crumbs.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top. Chill.
Will stay good for several days in refrigerator.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: Precook pierogies.
Cut venison into strips; lightly flour and fry in butter with seasonings and onion.
When done to your liking, add pierogies; fry until browned.
Add carrots and peas. Stir.
Fry only until peas are warm.
Serves 4.

title: fried rice
directions: In skillet, cook and stir rice in oil over medium heat until brown.
Add salt, water, bouillon and soy sauce.
Cover tightly. Simmer on low heat 20 minutes.
Add onions, celery, green peppers and meat.
Cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes longer or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: hobo bread
directions: Put the apples and baking soda in a bowl.
Pour the boiling water over them; stir and cover.
Let cool, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in the butter, sugar and egg; mix well.
Stir in the milk and then the flour; mix well.
The dough should be soft and moist like biscuit dough.
If it isn't, add a little more milk.
Put into an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pierogi(filled pasta)
directions: Knead all together making a stiff but workable dough.
(I put all the ingredients in the food processor and mix for about 1 minute.)
Then let stand for 30 minutes.
Divide in half and roll out very thin and cut into 2-inch squares.
Place a teaspoon of filling on every square and then fold each to make a three-corned shape, pressing edges well together.
Drop into boiling salted water; cook 15 minutes.
Drain.
Serve them sauteed until golden; garnish with some diced onion and bacon to your desire.

title: sangria wine cooler
directions: Mix in pitcher.
Serve with oranges and lime slices.
Makes 25 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form in patties.
Fry in margarine or shortening until golden brown, turning once.
Makes about 12.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat ground beef in bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish. Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat.
Add large bag mixed vegetables. On top of vegetables, add soup.
Cover with Tater Tots close together over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into crust.
Dot with butter.
Slit top.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup water (do not drain).
Put milk, cheese cubes and flour in blender.
Process at Grind.
Add mixture to broccoli.
Add chicken bouillon cubes and half and half.
Cook over medium heat until hot; stir frequently.
Mixture is ready when it thickens.

title: drop filled brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, soda-water mixture and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt; add to other mixture and blend. Drop by small spoonful on greased pan.
Make dent in top; put in 1 teaspoon filling.
Add teaspoon dough over filling (does not have to cover filling).
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Go over oysters carefully for shells.
Toast bread and crumble (about 2 cups).
Toss bread crumbs in melted butter.
Sprinkle a layer of crumbs in bottom of greased shallow dish; add a layer of oysters, another layer of crumbs and another layer of oysters, ending with buttered crumbs on top.
Use no more than 2 layers of oysters.
Combine remaining 7 ingredients together and spoon over oysters.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: okra goulash
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onion in drippings over medium heat, stirring constantly until tender.
Add okra and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add corn, tomatoes, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Pour in buttered baking dish and sprinkle with the bread crumbs and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Put in greased pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle on the lemon juice.
Combine cake mix, nuts and melted oleo until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cherries and bake in 350° oven until done.

title: red cross beans
directions: Brown sausage and onions. Drain fat. In a large casserole, place sausage and onions. Add beans and all other ingredients. It should be soupy. Bake at 325° for 4 hours.

title: monkey bread(mom)
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 quarters. Make balls. Mix cinnamon and sugar. Roll balls. Grease tube or Bundt pan with margarine; use a lot. Put balls in pan. Add nuts. Put 1 stick margarine and brown sugar in pan. Boil 1 minute. Pour over top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: pizza-style stuffed peppers
directions: Clean and prepare peppers for stuffing.
Steam peppers 5 minutes in vegetable steamer; drain.
Set aside.

title: honey cake from egypt
directions: Blend together butter and honey. Beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs. Mix together 1/2 teaspoon each cinnamon, nutmeg and mace, chopped dates or raisins, nuts and whole-wheat flour. Add to honey mixture.
Pour into lightly oiled baking pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. When cool, cut into 12 strips.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill overnight or 1 hour.
Roll in teaspoon size balls.
Roll balls in 1/4 cup of sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon mixed together.
Put on a cookie sheet and criss-cross with a fork, pressing cookie down before baking.
Bake 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: buttery walnut stuffing
directions: Turn crumbs into large baking pan and toast lightly in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes, stirring once or twice.

title: louise's fudge
directions: Boil
until mixture makes a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat; add Marshmallow Creme, butterscotch, chocolate chips and nuts if desired.
Mix together and pour into platter that has been greased with butter.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Boil together the sugar, lemon juice and pineapple for 5 minutes.
While mixture cools, mix the water and gelatine together; set it aside.
Mix the Dream Whip according to directions.
Add the cream cheese; whip until smooth.
Mix together the pineapple mixture and the gelatine.
When almost set, gently fold in Dream Whip mixture.
Let set overnight.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and stir until blended.
Grease two 9-inch pie plates.
Divide mixture evenly. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm of cold.

title: mosca's barbecue shrimp
directions: Combine unpeeled shrimp, 1 cup olive oil, garlic, bay leaves, rosemary and oregano and let stand at room temperature 2 hours. Turn into large skillet.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper and slowly saute shrimp, stirring some for about 20 minutes.
Cook slowly in shells until become thinly translucent and the shrimp bright pink on all sides.
Do not fry.
Add more oil if it evaporates.
Pour in wine, raise heat and simmer 7 or 8 minutes. Serve immediately with French bread for dipping in sauce.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Drain off juice.
Mix together with other, except flour, and keep out 1/2 cup vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes.
Stir almost continuously.

title: grandma's toast
directions: Cut crusts from bread slices.
Combine cream cheese, egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread on the bread slices.
Roll up like kieflies or crescent rolls.
Brush with melted butter. Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Roll each bread slice in the mixture.
Freeze on cookie sheets. Transfer into freezer bags.
When ready to use, bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, peanut butter and butter; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 30 minutes, or until firm.

title: souper burgers
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Stir to separate meat; spoon off fat.
Add soup, ketchup and pepper over low heat.
Heat through; stir soften. Serve on buns.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar, pudding and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs and add flour.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: jamaican curry chicken
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces (eg. thigh in two).
Mix all ingredients.
Heat oil in a large deep pot.
Cook on high heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer, covered, for about an hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.

title: chocolate coffee
directions: Mix chocolate syrup with coffee.
Beat cream into chocolate-coffee mixture.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: crunchy fruit and yogurt(low-fat)
directions: In small saucepan over medium heat, heat sugar and margarine until melted and thoroughly combined.
Stir in bran and pecans, tossing to coat well.
Cool.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in soup pot.
Drain pork on paper towel. Fry onions in bacon grease.
Return bacon to pot; add water and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add milk and fish.
Cook until fish is tender.
Do not boil.
Serve piping hot.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse and drain.
(Spaghetti should not be real dry.)
Dice green pepper, onion, cucumbers and tomatoes.
In bowl, mix spaghetti and diced ingredients.
Add salad seasoning and entire bottle of Italian dressing.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks.
Mash yolks with remaining ingredients except paprika until mixture is smooth. Fill egg whites with mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: aunt virginia's recipe for happiness
directions: Mix in love.
Add a lot of usefulness.
Season with smiles. Serve to everyone.

title: apple custard bread pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar; add melted butter, milk, nutmeg, vanilla and apples.
Place 1/2 bread in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 raisins.
Repeat bread and raisins.
Pour mixture over bread and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Before completely done, beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar and place on top of pudding.
Continue to bake until brown.

title: southern oven-fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip pieces in milk and coat with flour.
Dip into egg and coat with flour again.
Brown in small amount of oil.
Place pieces in pan and cook in a 300° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into freezer container and freeze according to freezer directions.
Let season.
Makes one gallon.

title: kathy janessa's herb bread
directions: *Leave the butter out so that it's very soft, or microwave it.

title: ham and lima salad
directions: Mix; season to taste.
Chill an hour or more before serving. The longer it sets, the better.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Grease baking container.
Put in a layer of tortillas.
Make 2 layers of each:
layer of chicken, 1 can mushroom soup, layer of onions, 1 can cream of chicken soup, layer of cheese and 1 can broth.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Take hands and squeeze Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour over mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken and pastry
directions: Cook chicken in a medium to large stock pot.
Season to taste. When chicken boils, start timing 20 to 30 minutes, checking with clean fork to see if tender (fork should slip through meat's thickest part easily).
Do not cook on high.
Chicken could easily boil over.
If chicken boils over, cut heat down immediately and tilt lid.

title: crispy chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and put
in
a 2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Combine and stir cereal, marshmallows and nuts together.
Pour melted bark over mixture; stir real good.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix and beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°, then for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat waffle iron and cook.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Wash and dry chicken, cut into bite size pieces.
Slice kielbasa into thin slices.
Saute chicken and sausage in sausage's own fat until chicken is brown on both sides.
Remove, set aside and keep warm.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Stir very well and drop by tablespoon on well-greased pan or griddle until brown.
Turn to brown both sides. When edges get crispy, they are great.

title: chicken divan(microwave)
directions: Mix melted butter, Parmesan cheese and dry bread crumbs together.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown beef.
Remove grease.
Add all other ingredients in large pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Makes 3 quarts and can be frozen for later use.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until golden.
Add meat and brown.
Transfer the meat mixture to a large saucepan and add remaining ingredients (except beans).
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until sauce is thick as desired (about 4 hours).
Add 2 cans kidney beans before serving. Cook them for 2 hours in the simmering sauce.

title: hamburger
directions: Put meat in round pan.
Fry in pan on stove.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Put catsup on it.
After it cooks, eat it in a bun.

title: sandra's sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange fruit in 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Sprinkle with 2/3 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Sift remaining dry ingredients in bowl.
Add oil, milk and egg and stir with a fork until blended.
Drop batter over fruit and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread i
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix cornbread according to package directions.
Add creamed corn.
Put 1/2 of the cornbread mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan top with meat and cheese mixed together. Put remaining cornbread mix on top of meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rocky road refrigerator dessert
directions: Prepare mix as directed on box for pie filling using 1 3/4 cups of milk.
Stir in half of whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts.
Place a single layer of graham crackers in bottom of 8-inch square baking pan.
Top with half of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate overnight.
Very good.

title: corn muffins
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add liquids to flour mixture and stir until ingredients are wet.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: salmon or tuna croquettes
directions: Preheat deep fryer half full of oil.
Drain all but 1/4 cup liquid off the salmon or tuna and set aside.
Put salmon or tuna in a mixing bowl and break it with a fork until no big flakes. Add flour, egg and pepper.
Mix well.
Add baking powder to liquid that was set aside and beat until frothy.
Pour into mixture and stir until well blended.
Scrape out a teaspoonful of mixture at a time and place in deep fryer of hot oil.
Watch closely because they brown quickly.
Lift out with slotted spoon and place on paper towel.
Serve and enjoy.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Place on top of mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover first 5 ingredients with water and cook until tender. Fry bacon, save 6 tablespoons drippings.
Make white sauce of drippings, flour and milk.
Add white sauce to soup, crumble bacon and add.
Heat thoroughly.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft. Combine all ingredients, except tortillas and picante sauce, using a potato masher.
Spread over flat tortillas.
Roll and place on paper towels.
Wrap, putting into a plastic bag.
Refrigerate for approximately 2 hours or overnight.
Slice to use as finger snack. Dip in picante sauce and enjoy.
Use within 2 days.

title: tuna pecan bake
directions: Combine mushroom soup, milk, tuna and peas. Fold in noodles and pour into greased quart casserole. Mix together equal parts of buttered breadcrumbs and pecans. Sprinkle evenly over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix with sugar, cocoa and milk over medium heat; bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix in oats, vanilla flavor and peanut butter.
Stir well and spoon onto greased aluminum foil.
Let stand.

title: zenith carrot pecan crunch pie
directions: If using fresh carrots, cook the carrots, covered, in about 1 cup water for 30 to 40 minutes, or until very tender.
Drain. Puree cooked or canned carrots in a blender, a food processor, or food mill until smooth.
You should have about 2 cups.

title: coot in cream gravy with green beans
directions: Rub the birds with cut lime pieces and set in refrigerator overnight.
Rinse and place in a pot.
Add enough salted water to cover.
Add celery and simmer until the meat is tender.
Add garlic powder and mushroom soup with stirring.
Stir in the sour cream and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Add the green beans and serve.

title: apple almond galettes
directions: Lightly flour a work surface.
Using light, even strokes, roll out half of the puff pastry dough to a 14-inch square about 1/8-inch thick.
Place a 6-inch pan lid on the dough and, using it as a guide, cut out 4 rounds with a small knife.
Sprinkle 2 baking sheets with water.
Set the rounds on one and press down slightly.
Prick each round with a fork in several places, but not near the edge.
Chill 15 minutes.
Divide the almond paste into 3 portions and roll each portion into a ball with your hands. Spread a sheet of parchment paper on the work surface.
Set 1 ball of almond paste on the paper and cover with another sheet of paper.
Roll the almond paste into a 5-inch round.
Set the round of almond paste on top of pastry dough round, leaving 1/2-inch border.
Repeat with remaining paste.
Refrigerate until ready to bake.
Cut the lemon in half and squeeze the juice from 1 half into small bowl.
Peel the apples, then halve and core them.
Rub with remaining lemon half to prevent browning; brush with lemon juice.
Heat oven to 425°.
Arrange apple slices, overlapping slightly, in a ring on the almond paste rounds, covering them completely.
Bake until the pastry edges have risen around the almond paste and are light and golden, 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle apples evenly with sugar.
Return to oven and continue baking until apples are golden brown, caramelized around the edges and just tender when tested with knife, 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: 24 hour omelette
directions: Spread bread with butter and cream cheese and cut into cubes. Place evenly in a well-greased casserole.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, pepper and chives.
Pour over bread cubes; add grated cheese.
Refrigerate covered overnight.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Continue baking uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Combine cheeses.
Sprinkle half on the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Beat eggs and sauce.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares (1/2-inch) and serve hot on tortilla chips.

title: apple sheet cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture and beat.
Fold in apples.
Add pecans; mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or bake in 2 greased layer pans for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: gooey chicken
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken breasts in dish.
Mix the soups together and pour over chicken breasts. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: spicy bites
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well.
Melt Velveeta (low heat).
When Velveeta is melted, add sausage and spices to taste.
Place bread on cookie sheets and top with mixture.
Bake in 400° oven for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter large cookie sheet generously.
In glass measure, place sugar.

Add corn syrup, water and salt; stir until well blended. With candy thermometer in place, microwave mixture on High power (100%) for 12 to 15 minutes, without stirring, until temperature reaches 300° (hard crack stage), just until caramel begins to turn light golden.
Watch closely; mixture burns easily.
To mixture, add peanuts, oleo and soda; stir well until peanuts are evenly coated.
Pour immediately onto prepared cookie sheet.
Spread to a 14 x 12-inch rectangle.
Let cool until firm.
With hand, break cold brittle into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: pepper jack stuffed chicken
directions: Cut cheese into 2 (2 1/4 x 1 x 3/4-inch) strips.
Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place a strip of cheese down the center of each chicken breast half; fold chicken over cheese and secure with toothpicks.
Rub seasoning over chicken.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil on all sides.
Transfer to a greased 8-inch square baking dish.	Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken juices run clear.	Discard toothpicks. Yield: 2 servings.

title: meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If mixture seems too dry, add a little more milk.
Shape into a loaf and bake in a flat dish at 325° for 1 hour 30 minutes or until done.
Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing. May pour 8 oz. can of tomato sauce over meat before baking.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice 4 large onions.
Pull apart in rings.
Dip in mixture. Let drain well.
French fry in oil heated to 375°.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add salt and pepper and put in casserole dish.
Add corn, tomato soup and precooked noodles. Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and add oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon, then add to egg mixture. Fold in zucchini and nuts.
Bake in two greased loaf pans at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quick sausage dinner
directions: In a Dutch oven, pour the potatoes and the green beans, draining one can of each first.
Add the smoked sausage.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 1 hour.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle spinach, cheese and onion in pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly and beat in remaining ingredients. Pour cream mixture in pie shell and stir gently.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll into ball the Roka Blue, Old English sharp cheese, cream cheese, vinegar and garlic powder.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: "jag" portuguese rice
directions: In a pot cook sausage with onion and season.
Follow directions for cooking rice in saucepot.

title: beef jerky or venison
directions: Cut jerky into 1/2 by 1/4-inch strips.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over meat.
Marinate overnight.
Remove from marinade and dry on paper towels.
Dry in oven until dry at 200° or dry on racks over wood stove.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat, onions and garlic until brown and onions are tender; drain.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Add egg, Ricotta or cottage cheese, Parmesan or Romano cheese and parsley.
Cook lasagna noodles following directions on package.

title: ruth neidlinger's fried chicken
directions: Parboil chicken for 40 minutes; cool.
Heat fryer to medium-high.
Make batter by mixing rest of ingredients (this should be a thinner batter than pancake batter).
Dip chicken into mixture, then fry for 5 to 7 minutes, until coating is cooked.

title: neck bones in barbecue sauce
directions: Wash neck bones.
Put small amount of oil in heavy pot or skillet.
Brown neck bones in oil.
Remove neck bones; place in a bowl.
Continue until all are browned.
Pour off fat; return bones to pot.
Cover with water.
Add dash of salt; simmer until almost done, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Remove to a baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven until slightly browned.
Pour on barbecue sauce and cook until slightly thickened.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well.

title: peanut butter penuche
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
In pan, combine granulated sugar, brown sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt. Cook and stir over medium heat until sugars dissolve and mixture begins to boil.
Reduce heat; attach candy thermometer to pan. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until candy thermometer reads 236° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, but do not stir it in.
Set pan aside; allow to cool undisturbed.
(Do not stir or move pan during cooling.) When thermometer reaches 115°, add vanilla. Beat by hand vigorously about 10 minutes, or until mixture starts to lose its gloss.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Score into small squares. When penuche is only slightly warm, cut or break into squares. Makes 2 pounds.

title: turkey almondine
directions: Roast turkey.
Cool and cut into cubes or cubed strips, not slices.
Melt 6 tablespoons of butter in Dutch oven.
Saute onions until golden.
Add mushrooms and saute for 4 minutes.
Remove onions and mushrooms.
Melt remaining butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add broth.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth and thick.
Stir in cream.
Add turkey, almonds, sauteed onions and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly.

title: idiots delight
directions: Melt morsels in top of double boiler.
Add noodles and peanuts, mixing well.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper and cool.

title: potato onion flat pie or au galette
directions: Heat butter and oil in large heavy skillet.
Add onions.
Cook, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until onions are tender. Add potatoes.
Cook, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes or until potatoes are translucent and onions golden.
Place unfolded pie crust on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread onion potato mixture over crust, leaving 1 1/2-inch border.
Fold border over filling.
Brush border with 2 tablespoons half and half.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining half and half with salt and pepper.
Pour over filling.
Bake 10 minutes more or until potatoes are tender and crust is golden.
Cut in wedges to serve.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl; stir in nuts and set aside.
In medium bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: 2 layer fudge
directions: Bring the sugar, oleo and milk to a boil and boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate bits, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Place flour and sugar in mixing bowl; set aside.
In saucepan, bring to boil butter, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well and add milk, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave hot bean salad
directions: Cut bacon strips into small pieces into 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes. Remove cooked bacon pieces to paper towel to drain.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper and vinegar to bacon drippings.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes until thick. Add drained beans and onion slices to sauce.
Cover, microwave 6 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: family favorite salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cook sugar and crushed pineapple until sugar dissolves. Prepare whipped topping according to directions.

title: nigerian chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save broth.
Debone chicken.
In a casserole dish, combine chicken, bay leaf, ginger, onion, red pepper, tomatoes and broth.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Make the night before and refrigerate.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Line with bread. Brown sausage and drain grease.
Mix with mustard and put over bread.
Lay slices of cheese over sausage.
Mix milk, half and half, eggs, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cheese layer.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak strips in hot fat.
Add sliced onion and crushed garlic; cook for 5 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Combine mushroom soup, mushrooms, catsup and Worcestershire; add to meat. Heat.
Serve over noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix together cornmeal, milk and egg.
Brown the meat; add onions and garlic.
Continue to saute until onions are soft.
Stir in chili powder, tomatoes, corn, beans and olives.
Heat for 5 additional minutes.
Stir in the cornmeal mixture.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 5 more minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8 for brunch, lunch or as dinner.
Serve with wilted spinach salad, broccoli spears and avocado slices.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vinegar in a deep bowl and stir until sugar dissolves.
Blend in onions, peppers, celery, pimento and caraway seed.
Add sauerkraut and toss to coat completely. Refrigerate overnight before serving.
This salad keeps well in refrigerator for a month or more.

title: citrus salad
directions: Combine oranges and pudding, mixing well.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Betty Crocker decorating stars at random for more color.

title: fluffy apple pancakes
directions: Saute in skillet the first 4 ingredients with the margarine (apples still firm).
Whisk together flour, salt, eggs and milk. Pour apple mixture in buttered baking dish.
Pour flour mixture over apples.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese cake
directions: Mix together margarine, cake mix and egg.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Then mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, egg and chocolate chips.
Pour this mixture over other mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: pizza casserole special
directions: Alternate layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in other ingredients, thoroughly.
Add crushed drained pineapple.
Sift flour; add remaining dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add raisins or dates and nuts; mix and pour into 4 small loaf tins that have been oiled and floured.
Turn oven to 325°.
(Do not preheat.) Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick, when inserted, comes out clean.
Let cool in the pan. Yield:
4 loaves.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar and vanilla and beat until thick.
Melt together butter and chocolate and add to egg mixture. Beat until smooth.
Add flour; mix and put in a greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm and remove from pan.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt morsels and butter over low heat.
Stir in cracker crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture firmly in pan.
Beat cream cheese, condensed milk, egg and vanilla in large bowl with mixer.
Pour over crumb mixture in pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over last layer.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Refrigerate.

title: fettucini supreme
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; drain and crumble.
Cook fettucini using package directions.
Drain and place in large serving bowl.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients; toss fettucini until coated.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: santa fe casserole bake
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat and stir until crumbly; drain fat.
Add taco spices and seasonings; blend well.
In small bowl, combine broth and flour.
Add to meat mixture; bring to a boil to slightly thicken liquid.
Stir in sour cream and chiles; blend well.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch lightly greased glass baking dish, place 1/2 of chips.
Top with 1/2 of beef mixture, 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of green onions.
Layer again with remaining ingredients, ending with green onions.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ring of tea biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together brown sugar, cream, butter, nuts and cherries.
Place in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart Bundt pan or salad mold. Dip each biscuit in butter and coat with cinnamon-sugar.
Place on top of contents in Bundt pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spray 2-quart oblong baking dish with vegetable cooking spray; arrange chicken, bone side down in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: easter bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, let raise.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
This can be frozen. Makes 2 gallons.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour.
Combine salt, cocoa, sugar and baking soda, then make 3 holes.
In first hole, put Crisco oil.
In second hole, vanilla.
In third hole, put vinegar.
Pour 1 1/2 cups water over mixture and mix well, then add 1/2 cup water and mix well.
Then add 1/2 cup water and mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Drain
liquid
from
peas and asparagus; mix liquid with cream of
mushroom
soup.
Set
aside.
Begin by covering dish with a layer
of cracker crumbs.
Add layer of peas, add layer of asparagus.
Continue this until you've used all vegetables. Add soup
mixture and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme mixing on medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Blend in sour cream; chill.
Serve as a fruit dip.

title: southern baked broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Season with salt and pepper. Spoon mixture into well-greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and top with stuffing mix. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit slush
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in a blender until smooth; pour into ice cube trays.
(This mixture can also be poured into popsicle molds and served as a healthy popsicle.)
Freeze until solid. Take frozen cubes and blend with enough mineral water to form a slush consistency.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pudding powder and all other ingredients, in a serving bowl, mix well.
Decorate with nuts and cherries and let set.

title: macaroni and cheese(microwave)
directions: Combine macaroni, 1 3/4 cups water and 4 tablespoons butter in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover and microwave at 100% power for 9 minutes.
Stir in half and half, salt, pepper, mustard and cheese until smooth.
Cover and microwave at 50% power for 5 minutes.
Toast bread crumbs in remaining 2 tablespoons butter in skillet over moderate heat.

title: onion-dill dip
directions: Stir together sour cream, onion, soup mix, parsley, garlic powder, dill weed and pepper until well blended.
Chill 1 hour. Makes 3 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion.
Add cooked macaroni and squash.
Add salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Spread over cream mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs 10 minutes.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to butter and sugar; then add the fruits, pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until done.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer in order.
Cover; refrigerate for 8 hours.
Mix before serving.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in a well-greased casserole (shallow) dish.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian meat balls
directions: *Add water to tomato paste.

title: quick coconut custard pie
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender.
Mix well.
Pour into a deep pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: verna's wild rice hotdish
directions: Mix rice and water and let stand 15 minutes.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Saute 3/4 c. celery and 6 Tbsp. chopped onion in butter and add. Put in casserole, sprinkle with 1/2 c. slivered almonds. Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Cover with crushed cracker and butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. You can add more or less to your taste.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: banana velvet
directions: Blend all except nutmeg in blender until smooth and creamy. Pour into chilled glasses.
Sprinkle each with desired spice. Serve with straws.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and place in the graham cracker pie crust. Makes a large pie.

title: divine divinity(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart glass measuring cup with handle, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Microwave at High for 5 minutes. Stir well until sugar dissolves.
Microwave at High for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture reaches 260°.

title: marinade for raw vegetables
directions: Note:
Use as much of the vegetables as you like.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce with watercress garnish.

title: gift of the magi bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter or margarine with granulated sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with bananas.
Stir in mandarin oranges, chocolate chips, coconut, 1/2
cup sliced almonds, cherries, and figs.
Pour into 2 greased 7 1/2 x 3 3/4 inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle remaining sliced almonds over tops.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
When cool, sieve confectioners
sugar over tops.

title: easy thousand island dressing
directions: Mix ingredients until blended.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Dresses up lettuce wedges and cold sliced turkey sandwiches.
Try it on your favorite tossed salad or hamburger, too!

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix the shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add egg. Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix into shortening and sugar mixture. Add coconut and banana flavoring.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: butterscotch cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
On low speed, beat in water and pudding mix until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
Garnish with coconut that has been lightly browned in oven.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Bone; cut into bite size pieces.
Line 2-quart shallow greased casserole dish with slightly crushed Doritos.
Put chicken and chopped onion on top.
Mix rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over chicken and Doritos.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's banana cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in bananas and vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: easy chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour and nuts with melted margarine.
Press down in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt shortening in a large saucepan.
Add brown sugar to shortening; blend well and cool 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/4 cups chocolate chips and nuts.

title: vegan lentil chili(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Soak the lentils overnight.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery (if used), then combine with lentils, beans, juice and tomatoes.
Add brown sugar to sweeten to taste.
Season with chili powder, some garlic powder, salt and cumin to taste.
Simmer an hour or so.

title: dog team tavern maple oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: bunny cake(a special easter treat)
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers according to package directions.
Cut cake as shown in diagrams.
Frost sides of each cake piece and

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put oats and vanilla in bowl; set aside.
Boil remaining ingredients for 1 full minute.
Pour over oat mixture, stirring to mix.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper and let get firm.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Beat ingredients 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: linda's stuffed potatoes(patata ripeni di linda)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Wash, scrub and dry potatoes. Bake potatoes for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool. Cut
potatoes
in
half and scoop out center, leaving a 1/4-inch shell on potato.
Combine scooped out potato and the rest of the ingredients and mix well by hand.
Fill the cavity of
the potatoes with filling, dividing evenly.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until heated thoroughly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put into an unbaked pie shell. On top, sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon mixed with 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles (about 1 hour).

title: chocolate marbles
directions: Put Oreos in food processor or crumble them up to "fine" consistency. Add cream cheese and mix well. Use about 1/2 teaspoon at a time and roll into little balls. Put on cookie sheet and put in fridge until very firm. Melt 1 block of paraffin and add chocolate chips. Dip cold balls (careful now) in the chocolate and lay out on wax papered cookie sheet until set.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until mixture forms a ball.
Knead dough.

title: sunny granola
directions: Combine all ingredients, except raisins; mix well.
Cook in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown; stir occasionally.
Stir in raisins.
Cool and store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 6 1/4 cups.

title: raisin pecan cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add extract and mix well.
Add coconut last.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Pour topping on while cake is hot and leave it in the pan for 1 hour.

title: have-a-cran-melon ball parfait
directions: Turn cranberry sauce into mixing bowl.
Beat until sauce is smooth.
Resting bottle on rim of bowl, slowly pour in lemon-lime beverage.
Mix gently with up and down motion.
Pour into 1-quart refrigerator tray and freeze.
Break into chunks.
Turn into chilled mixing bowl.
Beat until fluffy.
Return to tray and freeze.
Layer cranberry ice and honeydew balls in 4 chilled parfait glasses.
Serves 4.

title: reduced fat turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package until just tender; drain. Arrange broccoli in 1 1/2-quart casserole; lay turkey slices on top of broccoli.
Mix cornstarch with broth in saucepan until smooth.
Add milk; cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Remove from heat; add cheese and salt.
Stir until cheese melts. Pour sauce over the turkey.
Bake at 375° until sauce is bubbly about 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quiche
directions: In the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan, mix together the broccoli, mushrooms, shredded cheese and scallions.
Blend together the milk, Bisquick and eggs (in blender).
Pour mixture over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, add vanilla to eggs and beat slightly.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix.
Add melted butter and stir until smooth.
Cook on hot griddle at 400°.

title: navajo fry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Knead dough on a floured board until it becomes elastic.
Let dough rest 10 minutes, covered.
Roll out dough until it is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares or circles.
Deep fry at 370° until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Drizzle with honey and serve.

title: pioneer apple butter pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; add flour.
Add remaining ingredients and place in an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Additional cinnamon and spice may be added if desired.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except the nuts.
Chill.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Mix sugar and cream.
Melt over low heat until at soft ball stage.
Test in cool water.
Set aside to cool or place stewer in pan of cold water to cool quickly.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper until firm enough to remove.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg.
Stir in other ingredients.
Chill.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Serve at room temperature as a dip for apples, sliced and dipped in lemon water to avoid turning brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salt water until fork tender (do not overcook). Drain and cool. Alternate layers of carrots, bell pepper rings and onion slices. Beat remaining ingredients and pour over mixture. Cover and refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and cheese.
Melt butter; pour in stuffing mix.
Line casserole dish with 1/2 stuffing.
Add vegetables and soup mix.
Put stuffing mix on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: krispy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonful. Bake between 400° and 425° for approximately 10 minutes (watch).

title: strawberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add bananas and pineapple. Chill half of the mixture in 9 x 9-inch pan until firmly set. Spread evenly with sour cream and carefully pour in remaining jello.
Chill until firm.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sliced Bermuda onion and sliced tomato, in a bowl and mix gently.
Serve on a bed of lettuce and garnish with Bermuda onion and tomato.
Serve chilled.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix and stir all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: diet cake
directions: Freeze cake for easy slicing.
Mix Cool Whip and coconut. Drain pineapple; save juice.
Line deep dish with slices of cake. Sprinkle with pineapple chunks and spread with topping and coconut mixture.
Repeat with cake and topping, using juice on cake and end with topping.

title: dark chops and wild rice
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place pork chops on top; cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain liquid.
In large casserole dish, layer as follows.
Bottom layer:
tamales, then spread corn over tamales.
Next layer:
Add the tomatoes and salt and pepper to suit taste.
Cook in a 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly.
After removing from oven, add ground beef mixture and chiles on top.
Top with 2 slices of cheese.
Should melt; if not, place back in oven a few minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Pour onto hot waffle iron.

title: grandma's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed, then drain and cook rice as directed.
Mix broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz, soup, onions and celery until well blended.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together margarine and peanut butter. Gradually blend in the sugars until fluffy.
Add the egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add the baking soda and baking powder, mixing well.
Blend in the flour, mixing thoroughly. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten by crisscrossing with the tines of a fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken, skin and bone.
Dip tortillas in sauce.
Put chicken, Ortega peppers, sour cream, chopped green onions and cheese together.
Last, roll into a burrito in rectangle pan, continue.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas and top with strip of any leftover ingredients and cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven or until cheese melts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine, 3 tablespoons of sugar and crushed pretzels. Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Mix softened cheeses and onion together.
Form into ball.
Heat chopped beef in water and drain. Roll cheese ball in chopped beef.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt morsels with condensed milk and butter.
Remove from heat. In a large bowl, combine peanuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in wax paper-lined 9 x 12-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Remove from pan and peel off paper.
Cut into squares.
Cover and store at room temperature.

title: easy english muffins
directions: Mix yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and 3 cups flour.
Blend well, and beat vigorously until smooth.
Gradually add remaining flour to form a stiff dough, beating well.
Generously grease three (1-pound) coffee cans, sprinkle insides with corn meal.
Divide dough into 3 portions; shape each into a smooth round ball, and place in prepared cans. Let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
When cool, slice.

title: sea bass with mint
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).
Wipe fish with paper towels. Sprinkle inside and out with salt and pepper.
Chop 2 tablespoons mint leaves; reserve remaining leaves.
In a medium bowl, combine chopped mint, butter or margarine, bread crumbs, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stuff mixture into fish cavity.
Place fish in a baking dish; brush with olive oil.
Arrange remaining mint leaves; overlapping, to cover fish.
Pour wine around fish; cover with foil.
Bake in preheated oven 40 to 45 minutes or until fish turns from translucent to opaque and just begins to flake when pierced with a fork in thickest part.
Arrange mint sprigs along sides of a platter.
Place fish in center of mint.
Arrange lemon-slice quarters down center of fish.
Serve with a dry white wine.
Makes 2 servings.

title: mexican bake
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Cut biscuits into 16 pieces each.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread ingredients onto pan.
Bake for 40 to 55 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Take out at least 1/2 hour before ready to use.

title: mexi-taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Stir in soup, taco seasoning and beans.
Simmer while preparing topping.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over chops.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: butter egg bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, 3 cups flour and almond extract.
Mix well.
Add 1 stick melted butter and 1 beaten egg; mix well.
Add another egg and the other 3 cups flour. Knead well; let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour and 15 minutes).
Knead well again.
Make into loaves; let rise again for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then down to 300° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and make into rolls and place in the freezer. When ready to use, slice and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: rice and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter.
With a buttered casserole dish, put rice on bottom, then 1/3 of the cheese, tomatoes, onion, pepper and celery mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook soups, enchilada sauce and onion over low heat until ready to use.
Brown the ground beef.
Line a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish with layers of soup mixture, ground beef, tortillas and grated cheese.
Repeat until all is used, leaving grated cheese on top.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Arrange carrots in a vegetable steamer over boiling water. Cover and steam for 4 to 8 minutes or until desired tenderness. Remove from steamer, keep warm.

title: tuna pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, uncovered, before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs.
Drain spaghetti and place in a bowl with a lid.
Add the mushrooms, olives, onion, pepper and cucumber.
Mix well.
Add the dressing and place lid on the bowl.
Shake well.
Refrigerate and serve.
Great as a side dish or as a meal.

title: ham loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Shape into loaf (12 x 4 x 2-inches) in baking pan 9 x 13-inches.

title: orange jubilee(summer drink)
directions: Mix all ingredients and whip in blender.
Pour into tall glass and garnish with orange slice.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Set aside.
Blend margarine, shortening and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and nuts; mix.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Chop vegetables very finely and saute in butter.
Add crawfish tails and cook for 4 minutes.
Add soups and season to taste.
Then add cooked rice, water, parsley, and green onion tops.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake for 25 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Mix dry strawberry jello and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Add whipped topping.
Mix well again.
Add pineapple, fruit cocktail and nuts.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Keep refrigerated.
Ready to eat in minutes.

title: barbecued hamburg stacks
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Shape into 10 equal meat patties.
Combine bread cubes with milk, egg, shortening, 1/4 teaspoon of salt, marjoram and onion.
Shape into 5 bread patties.
Place 5 meat patties in a shallow baking dish.
Top each with a bread patty.
Place another meat patty on top of the bread.
Pour barbecue sauce over hamburg stacks.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes, basting often with sauce.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions together.
Pour boiling water over and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well, add sugar, salt and vinegar. Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until thick.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: parsley buttered potatoes
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13 pan with vegetable spray. Slice margarine and place over potatoes. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Sprinkle parsley flakes over top. Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender; stir gently once during baking.

title: sweet pickles
directions: *Always use bag salt.

title: bean soup(fassoulatha)
directions: Soak beans for 3 hours and drain.
Saute onions, garlic, carrots and celery in olive oil.
Add all ingredients to beans and water; cover and cook on low until beans are soft (about 3 hours). Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheddar balls
directions: Combine butter with cheese until smooth in a medium bowl. Blend in flour, salt and paprika, then knead lightly with hands to form a soft dough.
Roll into marble size balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 400° for 12 minutes until firm and golden.
Serve warm.

title: frank's healthy and good for you chili
directions: First, take a 4-quart nonstick Dutch oven and fry down the ground sirloin, the onions, the bell pepper and the garlic until the beef is browned and the vegetables are wilted.
Because you're not adding any fats or oils to the pot, and because you're using only the renderings from the ground sirloin, I suggest you do this over a medium heat so that the pot doesn't burn.
It's also a good idea to stir the mixture all the while it's cooking, too.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown oil, garlic and celery.
Mix rice, tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, bay leaf, cayenne pepper and 2 cups hot water and add to celery.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Brown the beef, add next 3 ingredients and combine with rice.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: chuck roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Allow 20 minutes per pound. Place roast in pan and brown on slow heat.
Add water and onion. Season with onion, salt, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Cook for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours on simmer.
Add potatoes and carrots during last hour.

title: five flavored pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs (well beaten).
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add flavorings to milk.
Alternate flour mixture with milk and beat.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions. Pour batter into 3 well greased and floured 8 or 9 inch layer pans. Cook according to package directions. Cool. Frost with caramel icing.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt butter on low
heat
in
saucepan.
Add
flour and salt, mixing well.
Allow
mixture to bubble 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add pepper, stock and cream.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, for about 15 minutes or until it is thickened and there is
no
starchy
taste.
Remove from heat. Add chicken and lemon juice.

title: chewy saucepan brownies
directions: Melt the butter and chocolate.
Stir in the following in order:
sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, salt and nuts. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375° until pulls away from side of pan. Cut into 2-inch squares. Enjoy!

title: lentil-spinach soup
directions: Wash and pick over lentils.
Place in boiling water and cook 2 minutes.
Cover; let sit 1 hour and drain.
(This removes gas.)

title: scallops in cream sauce
directions: Wash and pat dry scallops.
Heat vermouth and wine in saute pan.
Add scallops.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and keep warm.
Add shallots to saute pan.
Reduce to thick glaze.
Add cream and saffron.
Simmer until thickened.
Whisk in butter, a piece at a time.
Add salt and pepper.
Add warm scallops.
Serve in individual ramekins with rice on side and lemon wedges.
Serves 4 people.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Roll meat into balls.
Put onion into water and boil.
Add meatballs and boil 5 minutes.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to water and onion.
Simmer 2 hours.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; reserve some cheese to garnish top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, then uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well and put in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: baked jello mochi
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until there are no lumps. Pour mixture into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Leave foil on for 10 minutes after removing from the oven.
Do not cut into pieces for 24 hours.

title: brown sugar and nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugars and one egg at a time. Beat well.
Coat pecans with 1 tablespoon of flour and set aside. Mix flour and baking powder together.
Alternate with milk. Then add to other ingredients.
Fold in nuts. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread into small pieces and moisten with small amount of milk.
Add all of remaining ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine flour, 2 cups sugar, soda, eggs, vanilla, salt and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan. Remove from oven and prepare icing by cooking together the 1 cup white sugar, canned milk and margarine for 10 minutes after boiling starts.
Remove from heat and add coconut and nuts.
Pour hot icing over warm cake.

title: pie crust with vinegar
directions: Combine flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix with pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Beat remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Form into ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar together; set aside.
Mix pretzels and butter or oleo; press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spread cheese mixture over pretzels; spread Cool Whip over cheese.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot pineapple juice; add the strawberries.
Allow to set.
Pour over the top and refrigerate.

title: cinnamon chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.

Begin adding the eggs, sour cream, flour and baking soda until all mixed together. In a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 baking pan spread 1/2 the batter in the bottom, then sprinkle with 1/2 of the cinnamon & sugar mixture and add 1/2 of the bag of chocolate chips.
Add the rest of the batter on top of that and then sprinkle with the rest of the cinnamon & sugar and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: shrimp noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mix everything except salad greens; chill 2 hours, but no longer than 24.
Spoon onto salad greens.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix flour (self-rising) in milk.
Add to the mixture, pimentos, bell peppers, eggs (chopped), crab meat, shrimp, butter and 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle other half of the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix together tuna, cream cheese, onions and nuts. Shape into a ball and refrigerate 1 hour.
Then roll in chopped nuts.
Tastes better after sitting several hours.

title: curious caribbean punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix together pineapple juice, lemonade, orange juice, cranberry juice and apple juice.
Add the ice cubes. Float the lemon slices on top for garnish.
Very refreshing and pretty!

title: salsa
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: eggs hemmingway(brunch)
directions: Combine ingredients, except tomato and cheese, in greased casserole dish or pan.
Layer slices of cheese on top.
Slice tomato on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° (or less if glass dish) for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: oriental vegetable saute
directions: Saute the onions, celery and ginger root in the butter until onions are tender.
Stir in the water chestnuts, mushrooms, broccoli, red pepper (if used) and soy sauce.
Cover and steam for 5 to 8 minutes over medium heat or until vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into little balls.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zesty chicken taco rice salad
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil in a large skillet (or a wok works real nice) until lightly browned.
Add broth, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add corn and pepper; bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice; fluff.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips on the side.

title: creamy cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in a large sauce pan (cover with water) for about 15-20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Return potatoes to sauce pan and add milk and butter.
Beat with hand mixer until smooth.
Stir in cheese and season with salt and pepper.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with pastry blender until crumbly and add ice water.
Mix thoroughly, cover and refrigerate for at least an hour.
Prepare pie crust in usual manner.
May be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: dutch cheese wafers or apricot cheese wafer cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese in medium bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, apricots and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape dough into roll, 1-inch in diameter. Wrap in waxed paper and chill 3 hours or until firm.
Remove wax paper and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place one inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple-topped tortillas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large saucepan, combine apples, juice, sugar, and cinnamon; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until apples are tender and mixture is thick, 10-15 minutes.
Set aside.
Place tortillas on large baking sheet.
Bake until crisp and lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Let cool; top with apple mixture.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after adding each one.
Add flour containing baking powder alternately (one cup at a time) and milk (1/2 cup at a time), starting and ending with the flour.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.

title: mexican crescent pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add seasoning and water.
Combine black olives, onion, sour cream and mayo in bowl.
Separate dough into triangles and place in ungreased 10-inch pie plate or 8 x 12-inch glass pan.
Spoon burger over crust.
Add tomatoes and 1 C. cheese. Spread sour cream mixture over the burger and then add remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-35 minutes.
Serve with salsa.

title: punch
directions: Three recipes make 200 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour and cocoa. Mix well.
Add pecans. Pour in a greased cookie sheet and bake for about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat vegetable lasagna
directions: Arrange first four ingredients in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender; drain and transfer to a boil; set aside.

title: tasty meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients into balls.
Mix last ingredients together and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir
boiling
water into corn meal.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour
into
greased
2 quart casserole.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 to 45 minutes or until just set.
Serve hot with butter and warm maple syrup.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet-sour chicken wings
directions: Arrange chicken wings in shallow container.
In medium size bowl, combine orange juice, soy sauce, brown sugar, cranberry sauce and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Pour sauce over chicken wings. Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Turn wings occasionally to marinate evenly.
Lift wings from marinade and place on a shallow baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Baste frequently with reserved marinade during baking.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: cooked dressing(for potato salad, cole slaw, fresh lettuce, onion and egg salad.)
directions: Cook 2 or 3 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Stir constantly (sticks quick).
When cool, add 1/2 cup canned milk.
Add mayonnaise and celery seed to taste.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Sift flour and meal together.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Add melted Crisco and cracklings.
Mix all together.
Bake at 400°.

title: easy brown rice and mushrooms
directions: Brown rice in margarine.
Add mushrooms and ground round (which has been browned and drained).
