Add soup and 1/2 can water with some pepper for taste.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and cover. Cook on low heat for about 45 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: lemonade pie(cool and refreshing)
directions: In a medium size mixing bowl, combine lemonade with condensed milk.
Fold in prepared whipped topping and mix well.
Pour into crust and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
In a separate bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Stir in cream cheese mixture. Put in pan and freeze overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: easy appetizer
directions: Place cream cheese on plate and pour Pickapeppa sauce over top. Serve with crackers. Easy and attractive!

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix whole thing on low speed. Then at med. speed for 2 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Mix okra, salt and apple cider vinegar.
Put in a container and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, or until okra changes color.
Put in jars and seal up.
When you open, rinse off, let drain, cover in meal and fry.
You can also add to vegetable soup.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute butter and onions.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup, cooked rice and cooked broccoli.
Mix well and bake in casserole dish for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions.
Cook until light brown.
Sprinkle in flour.
Add broth, water and bay leaf.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Put bread cubes on top.

title: sugar-free punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare all above mixes.
Slice cake in thin pieces when cooled.
Slice all kinds of fruit.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Then add onions and zucchini.
Mix.
Add oil and eggs.
Mix well and put in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in a small amount of oil.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 325° in oven, uncovered.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crispy crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and egg.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add alternately to mixture with the cup of pumpkin.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sardine caper spread
directions: In
bowl,
mash sardines with a fork, then mix in cream cheese, capers, lemon and pepper to taste.
Serve as spread on crackers.

title: more casserole
directions: Melt fat and saute onion and garlic lightly.
Do not brown. Add ground beef and saute.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and water. Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms, peas, corn, salt and pepper.
Heat.
Add cooked spaghetti to sauce and blend well. Fill large greased baking dish with 1/2 of mixture.
Add 1/2 of cheese and remainder of mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: allspice pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in oil.
Slice onion and put a slice on top of each chop.
Mix together seasonings and sprinkle over chops and onion.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 45 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Tie spices in a cheese cloth or place in a tea ball.
Add cider along with the sugar and whole oranges.
Heat to boiling; turn down heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add shortening and mix with fork until mixture looks like fine cornmeal, then add to egg, water and vinegar.
Shape into 4 balls and chill before rolling.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Set aside.

In 2-quart shallow baking dish, arrange chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover and spoon soup mixture over chicken. Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Makes 4 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In large bowl combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, allspice, ground black pepper, nutmeg, milk and egg.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In a large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Add meatballs, brown on all sides.
Remove from pan.
Set aside.
To the drippings in skillet, stir flour until smooth.
Gradually add beef broth, cream and a pinch of pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add meatballs, reduce heat and simmer, covered, until meatballs are cooked through, approximately 15 minutes.
Yields 50 meatballs.

title: 5-minute tuna
directions: Drain tuna and slice radishes.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine the tuna, radishes and macaroni salad.
If necessary, stir in 1 tablespoon mayonnaise or salad dressing to moisten.
Makes 2 servings.

title: bennett a la king
directions: Cut turkey or chicken into small pieces.
Place in 4-quart saucepan.
Add water, garlic, onion soup mix and salt and pepper. Cook until meat is tender.
Drain vegetables and add to turkey or chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Cook at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes and serve over rice or toast.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken in lime
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken pieces and cook over medium heat until both sides are brown.

While chicken is browning, cut onion coarsely and put garlic through press; add to chicken. Add red pepper, cumin, coriander seed, turmeric and soy sauce. Reduce heat; cover and cook until chicken is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut 1 lime into quarters.
Just before serving, sprinkle chicken with the juice of 1 lime (about 2 tablespoons).
Serve with lime quarters.

title: green bean meal in a pot
directions: Put green beans in a large pot and cover with water.
Cook 1 hour (add water to keep covered).
Add pork chops and cook 1 hour. Add salt to taste.
Add potatoes.
Cook slowly, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on potatoes.
Beans should not boil completely dry.

title: mexicana rice
directions: * More or less to suit preference.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Add sour cream and milk; beat at low speed.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add to mixture.

title: winter salad with walnuts and apples
directions: Combine salad, apples, walnuts and Blue cheese.
Whisk together oil and vinegar; pour over salad.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: shrimp boat texas-style
directions: Melt butter; add onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add shrimp and saute for 4 more minutes until pink. Cut French bread in half lengthwise.
Pull out all of the bread from the center of loaf.
Toast bread from center and crumble. Add toasted bread to shrimp mixture and stir until bread absorbs liquid.
Spoon mixture into bread.
Top with cheese and black and green olives.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dump in a box of cake mix; dot top with margarine.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Use a little butter to grease 9-inch square pan.
Put bread in pan.
Mix together pineapple, eggs, sugar and milk.
Pour over bread.
Drizzle rest of butter on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is nicely browned.

title: phyllis' baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onions.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brown sugar pies
directions: Keep the egg whites to go on top.
In a saucepan, mix sugars, flour and egg yolks.
Mix in milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When thick, add margarine and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shells.
Top with beaten egg whites in which 1/4 cup sugar has been added.
Brown under broiler in oven.
Real good pies.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour into jars and let cool with lids off.
Then refrigerate. Makes 5 1/2 small jars.
Makes great gifts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine in casserole dish; bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Boil until mixture makes soft ball when dropped in cold water. Stir in 2 cups pecans.
Drop each pecan on waxed paper, separately.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Have prepared a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, greased and floured. In large bowl, mix all ingredients except raisins and nuts.
Beat at low speed until well mixed, scraping sides of bowl frequently. Beat on high speed 3 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Add raisins and nuts which have been coated with a bit of flour.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost with your favorite caramel icing.
Serves 12.

title: peppernuts
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add syrup, cream and eggs.
Mix well. Sift spices with flour and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients and anise oil to creamed mixture.
Mix well.

title: fried peanut butter and banana sandwich
directions: Spread bread with peanut butter and banana.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Fry sandwich, browning it on both sides.
Serve warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken to tender.
Drain.
Tear chicken from bone.
In medium bowl, mix chicken soup, mushroom soup, cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix seasoning from stuffing with this.
Put in torn chicken; add all together.
Place in a casserole dish, then sprinkle your stuffing crumbs over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot enough to see bubbling around edge.

title: creek fried potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into thin squares.
Dice onion into small pieces.
Grease a large baking dish with oil or nonstick spray.
Layer the bottom of the pan with bacon, 1/2 potatoes, onion and 6 slices Velveeta.
Repeat again, starting with bacon.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Put potatoes in casserole dish.
Brown onions in bacon grease.
Stir in flour.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar. Cook until thick.
Add crumbled bacon.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Pour over potatoes and punch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab crostini
directions: In a medium bowl, combine crabmeat, red pepper, mayonnaise, parsley, chives, lime juice, mustard and hot sauce; blend well.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cup sugar in the 7 cups water, stir until dissolved. Add potatoes, cook until fork tender, drain and reserve the water. Melt 1 stick of butter in a sheet cake pan, set aside.
Combine the flour,1 cup sugar, milk and vanilla, mix well.
Pour the batter into the sheet cake pan over the butter.
(Do not stir.)
Lay potatoes on batter, pour the reserved water from potatoes over mixture (don't stir).
Bake in 400 degree oven for 45-50 minutes until browned.

title: jam cake(makes 3 layers)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Let stand until it foams.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add one cup at a time to other mixture and beat. Add buttermilk, a little at a time, then fold in the jam last. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes a very large cake.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Add pineapple to cheese. Mix pepper, pimento, onion and salt into cheese mixture.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Form into 2 large balls. Cover each with remaining nuts.
Chill in refrigerator.
Garnish with parsley and maraschino cherries.

title: play dough
directions: Stir over low fire.
Knead in color.

title: chocolate pecan caramel candies
directions: On waxed paper, place pecan halves in pairs 2-inches apart. In a heavy saucepan over medium-low heat, cook and stir the caramels and milk until melted. Pour about 2 teaspoons of caramel mixture over each pair of pecans. Let stand until set. With buttered fingers, shape pecan clusters into balls. Dip in candy coating. Place on waxed paper-lined baking sheets. Refrigerate until set. Store in an airtight container. Yield: about 5 dozen.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar.
Mix well until dissolved.
Stir with popcorn and peanuts.
Store in airtight container.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut unpared potatoes into 1/4-inch-thick slices. Place overlapping slices in buttered oven-to-table 13 x 9 inch baking dish.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix to creamy consistency the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add one whole egg at a time and beat.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder, then add flour mixture alternately with milk to butter and sugar mixture.
Add flavoring.
Line bottom of tube pan with waxed paper and grease sides of pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in pot and boil for 1 hour, then place in a shallow pan and pour sauce over ribs and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in oven or place on outdoor grill for 45 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onions, bell pepper and celery until tender.
Add any crawfish fat and let cook 15 to 20 minutes on low.
Add crawfish tails and cook another 15 minutes.
Season well.
Serve over rice.

title: wedding cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pineapple and juice and nuts together.
Add flour and baking soda; mix well.
Grease and flour pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or in sheet cake pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to instructions (in one layer).
When done, use a fork and punch holes into the cake.
Mix cream of coconut with milk.
Pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and moisten coconut flakes.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Bring Karo, margarine, sugar and salt to boil on medium heat. Add peanut butter and stir constantly until creamy.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered baking dish and cool.

title: chicken filled dumplings
directions: Put both cans of soup in pot with 1 1/2 to 2 cups water.
Roll out biscuits.
Mix the chopped ingredients and put 1 to 2 tablespoons in the center of biscuits and pinch edges together. Have the soup mixture bubbling and drop in biscuits.
Cover with lid; lower heat.
Stir occasionally.
Cook for about 25 minutes.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Melt margarine; add ground beef, stirring, until browned and crumbly.
Add onion and celery; stir often for five minutes. Break up tomatoes with spoon and add to meat.
Add water, beans and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Add cabbage.
Reduce heat and simmer until cabbage is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add lime rind and juice. Beat egg yolk slightly; slowly add gelatin, stirring constantly. Add milk and bitters, stirring until blended.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat egg white until stiff peaks form.
Fold into Jell-O mixture.
Add food coloring.
Pour into pie shell. Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip and lime slices, if desired.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Mix together in another bowl the flour, salt and cocoa.
Set aside. Add the buttermilk, vanilla and food coloring slowly.
Then fold in the dry ingredients.
Add the soda and vinegar.
Mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Combine together flour, eggs and sugar.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla.
Bake in pie shell at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken parmesagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Dip chicken in eggs, then bread crumbs.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Arrange chicken in 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese and 1/2 parmesan cheese.
Pour Ragu sauce over chicken; sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon pecan fruitcake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and remaining ingredients.
Use greased tube pan.
Put pan of water under cake in oven.
Bake 2 hours and 30 minutes in a 250° to 275° oven.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Combine maple syrup, cornstarch and salt.
Stir into pineapple liquid.
Add vinegar and soy sauce.

title: dill dip for bread
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.
Use one loaf Swedish rye bread.
Cut round out of center to form bowl to put dip in.
Tear up bread and use for dip.
Also use vegetables (carrots, cucumber, broccoli or cauliflower).

title: head cheese
directions: Boil meat until it falls off of the bone.
Chop or grind meat and add black pepper, salt, allspice and cloves according to your taste.
Mix with broth in which meat was cooked and cook for 20 minutes.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a large
bowl
dissolve yeast in warm water or milk. In a medium-sized saucepan melt butter in milk, bring to boil. Remove from stove	to
cool
to
lukewarm.
Add
to yeast with sugar, salt and
eggs (slightly beaten).
Mix well.
Gradually add enough flour to
make
a
soft
dough.
Let rise to double (about 2 to 3 hours).
Punch
down
and
knead for 5 minutes. Form into small balls
for	round rolls or roll out on floured board and cut with a
biscuit cutter and fold over for Parker House rolls.
Let rise to	double	(about	1 to 1 1/2 hours). Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Pour into dish and bake at 350° until set. Remove and cover with crushed chips or Cheez-Its.
Bake until light brown.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into ball.
Chill overnight.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in large bowl lettuce, spinach, celery, water chestnuts and peas.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, Parmesan cheese, salt and garlic powder; mix well.
Spread on top of layered salad.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with eggs, bacon and tomatoes.

title: casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add next 7 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Parboil apples.
Wrap in pie dough; pour syrup over.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Use whipping cream, if desired.

title: lazy man's cabbage rolls
directions: Slice cabbage and place on bottom of casserole.
Brown meat; drain.
Add rice and soup mix.
Place on top of cabbage.
Mix soup and water together and pour over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put all ingredients into large cooker.
Let this cook until it changes color.
Put into jar while hot.
Seal.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and water.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Wrap with aluminum foil 1 carrot, 1 potato, 1 onion and 1/2 of ground beef. Do the same with the other half. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 1 hour at 375°.

title: delicious cheddar cheese soup
directions: Cook all vegetables in water; steam until tender.
Add all the cheeses and butter until melted.
Stir constantly.
Turn off stove. Add flour to milk until no lumps are visible.
Pour this into the vegetable and cheese stock.
Stir well and cover kettle; let stand for 5 minutes.
Important:
Be sure your burner is off and soup is not boiling when you add the milk mixture, as this will make it curdle.
The heat of the covered pot will make it thicken.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook breasts of chicken in pressure cooker for 15 minutes with 1 cup water.
Cool immediately.
Remove skins and bones; cut into small pieces.
Pour the juice of 2 lemons over the meat and place in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, add the onion, which has been diced, almonds, celery and grapes and season to taste. Moisten well with mayonnaise.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Garnish with ripe olives and tomato wedges.
Serves 8.

title: quick and easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Place biscuits in pie dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake as can directs.
Glaze while hot.

title: dorothy's beans
directions: Saute onion in bacon fat.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or at 250° for 3 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook
together	beans
and minced onion in butter until onions are
tender.	 Add
flour,	paprika,
mustard, Worcestershire sauce
and
half and half to hot onion mixture. Pour the
cheese mixture over the beans which have been placed in a
buttered
casserole.
Cover
with
cup finely crushed potato chips.
Bake
until bubbly and brown in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: grilled halibut
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the halibut, to make a marinade.
Marinate the halibut in the refrigerator at least 1 hour, turning at least once.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain 16 ounce can salmon and remove skin and bones.
Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Brown in a lightly greased skillet on both sides.

title: papas fritas(fried potatoes)
directions: Wash and peel potatoes; slice very thin.
Heat drippings or oil over medium-high heat in skillet.
Cook potatoes until golden brown on one side.
Turn potatoes and smother with onions.
Turn once more to mix potatoes and onions.
Season with salt and pepper; serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; beat until firm.
Line crust with bananas that have been soaked in lemon juice to keep them from turning dark.
Put some on bottom.
Pour filling on them and decorate with bananas.

title: taco casserole
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and drain ground beef.
Add taco sauce to beef.
Line a greased pan with crescent roll.
Pinch all holes closed.
Spread 1/2 of meat on top of crescent roll.
Then layer 1/2 of the tomatoes and onions.
Next layer will be 1/2 of the chips, then 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: caviar appetizer
directions: Quantities of ingredients to be determined by size of dish.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet (11 x 15) with dough, pat to fit. Bake 7-8 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool. In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, cream cheese and dressing mix. Spread over cooled crust. Toss vegetables in a large bowl and spread over cream cheese mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. (Overnight is better). Cut into bars and serve.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk and sugar to make batter.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour batter into dish.
Spoon peaches and juice evenly over batter.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until batter rises up and around the fruit.

title: white chili
directions: Combine beans, stock, 1/2 the onion, garlic and salt in a large kettle and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Remove from heat and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: curried butternut squash soup
directions: Heat oil in large Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add leek, curry powder, sugar, cumin, red pepper and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add squash, water, apples and apple juice.
Bring to the boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until squash is tender.
Place half of soup in a blender and process until smooth.
Pour pureed soup into a large bowl.
Repeat procedure with remaining soup.
Return soup to pan. Stir in cream and salt.
Cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated. Garnish each serving with about 1 tablespoon of cilantro or parsley.
Yield: 10 one-cup servings.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Mix in large bowl.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Turn kraut into colander and let drain thoroughly. Combine all ingredients in bowl and chill for 6 hours or overnight.

title: monica's crab balls
directions: Place egg, bread, spices and oleo in blender and mix.
Place in bowl and add cleaned crab meat.
Make into 2-inch balls.
Broil at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn to brown all over.
Cool.
Place on tray, then put in freezer.
When frozen, put in airtight container and keep in freezer until needed.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Dissolve drink mix in cold water. Add sugar and stir well. Add pineapple juice and gelatin. Refrigerate.
Add 7-Up and sherbet when ready to serve.
Serves 35 people.

title: oatmeal fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Mix brown sugar, 3/4 cup margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in baking mix and oats until of uniform consistency.
Heat chocolate chips, milk, 2 tablespoons margarine and salt in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Press about 2/3 of oatmeal mixture with greased hands in pan. Spread chocolate mixture over oatmeal layer.
Drop remaining oatmeal mixture by tablespoons onto top.
Bake about 30 minutes. Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: granny gertie's lye soap
directions: Build a fire around a kettle and cook all ingredients.
Set off and stir until it gets hard.
Pour into pan or cut out of kettle.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Roll in flour.
Lightly brown in grease on top of stove. Remove meat.
Place in casserole dish.
Place soup and broth over meat and cook for 1 hour at 350° or desired tenderness.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: tacos
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add onion, garlic salt, cumin powder, chili powder and red pepper.
Cook until meat is well done, stirring occasionally.
Simmer about 5 minutes.

title: cashew chicken(serves 4)
directions: In small bowl, combine garlic, honey, soy sauce and ginger.
In 11 x 7-inch baking dish, arrange chicken.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons garlic mixture over chicken.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Spoon juices over chicken halfway through.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in bowl as listed.
Combine, seal and refrigerate for 10 hours or more.
Toss and serve.

title: cobbler cake
directions: Melt margarine in an oblong cake pan.
Mix in bowl the flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Spread in cake pan.
Spoon fruit on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot tomato relish
directions: After cooking, take 3 to 4 cups and put into blender to thicken.
Add back and cook until it has cooked down and about 1/3 of ingredients are left.

title: turkish delight
directions: Blend together 8 envelopes unflavored gelatin and 2 c. sugar in 2 1/2 quart saucepan.
Stir in water and salt.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin and sugar are dissolved. Let simmer 20 mins, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in orange juice concentrate.
Chill, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in nuts.
Line an 8 inch square pan with waxed paper.
Turn mixture into pan and chill until firm.
Unmold on board dusted with confectioners sugar.
Cut candy into squares and roll in sugar.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: cocoa mix
directions: *Equivalent amount of Equal or Sweet 'N Low may be substituted for sugar.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets.
Combine with chopped onion, diced carrots, raisins and crumbled, cooked bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and toss at least one hour before serving.
Sprinkle sunflower seeds on top.

title: burrito de manzana(apple-filled tortillas)
directions: Peel and cut apples into small pieces.
Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon together.
Warm tortillas until they are soft and flexible.
Put a large heaping spoonful at one end of the tortilla and roll, folding in the ends.
Close with a toothpick.
Deep fry burrito until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar and serve warm.
This can be done with other pie mixtures, too.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together in pot and cook until soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
When it reaches soft ball stage, take off stove and mix in peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Beat until starts to thicken.
Pour out on buttered dish to cool.

title: lois' cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternating with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Put a layer of batter, then half the cranberry sauce, rest of batter and cranberry sauce.
Top with walnuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Drizzle topping on while warm.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together and heat sugar, water, cinnamon, nutmeg and oleo. Double this if you like a "gooey" sauce; we do.

title: skillet pot roast
directions: Preheat electric skillet, uncovered, at 325°.
Brown roast for 5 minutes per side.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Sprinkle roast with seasoned salt and pepper, onion soup mix and onion.
Roast, covered, with vent closed for about 2 1/2 hours.
Turn after 1 hour.
Vegetables, such as quartered potatoes or cut carrots, may be added at this time.
Juices that accumulate may be used for gravy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Shape by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Place in ungreased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake for 45 minutes covered with foil.
Uncover and continue baking for 15 minutes longer.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and green peppers.
Add ground beef and cook until lightly browned.
Add soups and water and heat.
Blend with 1/2 cup cheese and cooked noodles in 3-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Or, just blend 1 cup cheese in with cooked noodles and put none on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: pork steaks
directions: Fry chops; brown.
Combine ingredients.
Pour over chops. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered.
May need to add a little water.

title: squash dressing
directions: Drain squash and mash. Melt butter and saute onions. Add soup and water; mix well. Add bread and mix together. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chinese fish with vegetables
directions: Clean and bone	fish;
cut into 1-inch squares.
Dredge lightly in the 3
tablespoons cornstarch.
Heat oil in a large skillet or wok
until
hot,
but not smoking.
Toss vegetables with garlic and ginger
in hot oil until tender-crisp, about 2 minutes.
Push aside
and add fish pieces; stir-fry until fish is opaque, another 2 minutes.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Grease a large bowl.
Set aside.
Heat milk, water and butter in saucepan until very warm.
Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in mixing bowl.
Add heated mixture and egg.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Cover with bowl.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into ball.
Place in prepared bowl.
Turn once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size. Punch down.
Grease 24 muffin cups.
Pinch off pieces of dough and shape into balls.
Place 3 in each cup.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chicken bow tie soup
directions: Marinate the chicken in orange juice, lemon juice, honey and spices.
Braise chicken, then add to soup.

title: amish pudding
directions: Mix dates, soda and warm water and let stand while mixing the following.
Mix together butter, egg, nuts, sugar and flour with above.
Bake in a greased and floured 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Make pudding according to package and fold in Cool Whip. Crumble cool cake and place a layer of cake in a large bowl.
Add a layer of pudding.
Repeat until all is used.
Better if sets overnight.
Serves: 10 to 15.

title: jaime's blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar very well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to batter alternately with milk.
Add blueberries by hand.
Grease top of muffin tin and use paper cup liners; fill full.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until nicely brown.

title: chopped eggplant
directions: Microwave eggplant, one at a time, for 15 minutes.
If not completely soft, add a few minutes.
Poke them first to let steam escape.
When cool, scrape flesh from skin and chop well.
(This can be done in a 350° oven, but microwave retains lovely celadon green color!)

title: bread
directions: Mix water and yeast together.
Add rest of dry ingredients, egg and Crisco (except flour) and beat with mixer.
Add 3 cups flour and beat with mixer again.
Add the rest of flour.
If sticky, add more flour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 2 to 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: brown sugar coconut frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread over Lazy Daisy Oatmeal Cake.
Broil until bubbly.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In large bowl stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate chips, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pistachio sour cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream and water. Blend to moisten, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Makes one 10-inch cake.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Blend in order as listed; pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This is good for Christmas.

title: giblet gravy
directions: In a pot bring 2 cups of broth to a boil.
Add cut up giblets. In measuring cup, add 1 cup of warm water.
Stir in cornstarch until it is not lumpy.
Add to broth and stir constantly.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Cut cranberry sauce into cubes.
Drain pineapple.
Beat together
sour cream, cheese and dash of salt.
Fold in chicken, pineapple, celery, nuts and green pepper.
Refrigerate up to
24 hours.
Before serving, top chicken mixture with cranberry cubes. Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: hot dogs
directions: I make 'em on the grill.
They come from the "Acame."

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Top with chopped nuts and serve with apple wedges.

title: bacon and chive potato salad
directions: Add potatoes to boiling water.
Cook 14 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard in large bowl.
Add potatoes, bacon and chives or onions.
Mix lightly and refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.
Each serving counts:
1 bread, 2 fats, 42 optional calories.

title: dixie spoon bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add boiling water and blend. Add butter, beaten egg yolks and buttermilk.
Blend.
Fold in egg whites lightly but thoroughly and bake in a 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: remarkable crab dip
directions: Sift through crabmeat to get as many shells out as possible. Put cream cheese in a large bowl and let soften. Add crabmeat, sour cream, cream cheese, dry mustard and Mozzarella cheese. Stir until completely combined. Add Old Bay to taste. Bake in an ungreased casserole dish at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian meat balls and spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix well and shape into balls.
Brown in skillet and drop into sauce; simmer along with sauce.

title: taco casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and onion until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning.
Heat through. Remove from heat.
Beat eggs, stir in milk and add small amount tomato sauce to egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Return to skillet.
Stir in beans, the 1 1/2 cups cheese and crushed tacos. Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Top with lettuce, 1/2 cheese, olives and tomato.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting in squares.

title: korean coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Crumble Ramen noodles (uncooked) and add to cabbage.
Mix in seeds and nuts.

title: crab spread
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and all ingredients except nuts and paprika.
Spread into a 9-inch pie pan.
Top with walnuts and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serve with crackers.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve.

title: fruit spread
directions: Mix and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Spread on any fruit. Mixture will be thick.

title: turkey grape salad
directions: Combine turkey, celery, grapes and mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Season with salt and pepper. Toss lightly.
Serve on greens; trim with grapes.
Makes 6 servings.
May add nuts.

title: olive filled cheese balls
directions: Beat together cream cheese and butter until well blended and creamy.
Stir in flour and cayenne.
Wrap a teaspoonful of dough around each olive, covering completely.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes about 25 appetizers.

title: basil salad dressing, maui style
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender until smooth. Pour into a clear glass jar.
Refrigerate up to 10 days.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion; add to squash, flour, salt and herb. Beat eggs lightly; add sour cream and add to squash mixture. Add cheeses.
Top with bread crumbs mixed with extra Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crisp pickles
directions: Mix together; let stand 3 hours, covered with ice.
Drain.

title: millie's roll-ups
directions: Spread dressing and salsa on each tortilla; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with lettuce and meat.
Roll up.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a large pot with tight lid combine sugar, syrup and water; cover pot and cook on high heat.
Takes 5 minutes to boil.
Place candy thermometer heat 230°; add peanuts or coconut.
Stir with metal spoon.
Boil to 300°; takes about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and baking soda.
Stir.
Cool 1 hour. Crack and serve.

title: filled cookies
directions: Put all dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add butter and shortening.
Mix with pastry blender.
Add eggs and flavoring.
If too dry, add milk.
Roll and cut with a doughnut cutter cutting a hole in the top layer only.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers overnight in a brine of 1 cup salt to 1 gallon water.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Mix creamed butter and sugar until smooth.
In a medium bowl, mix flour, baking soda, and salt.
Add this mixture to sugar mixture.
Stir in oats.
Press half in greased 13x9 inch pan. Spread jam on top of mixture and then add remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in oleo. Add onion and celery. Add rice, pepper, water and soy sauce. Bake at 350°. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: saucepan banana fudge walnut brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and chips.
Mix dry ingredients together and add all ingredients to mixture in saucepan, stirring enough to blend well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost, if desired.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: In buttered 9-inch square baking dish, layer broccoli, chicken bread cubes and cheese.

title: nutter butter creamy crisps
directions: Spread peanut butter between two ritz crackers. Dip in melted chocolate candy. Cool on waxed paper. Drizzle melted white chocolate across tops. Enjoy!

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir in fruit and vanilla.
Freeze according to package directions.

title: easy lasagna casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions and pour off grease.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add evaporated milk to drained noodles and 2 ounces or 1 small package of softened cream cheese. Pour noodles into a 2-quart casserole or oblong pan.
Spread meat mixture over the noodles.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: country fried venison steaks
directions: Cut venison steaks into serving size pieces; coat both sides with salt, pepper and flour.
Brown on both sides in bacon grease; cover with onion slices; add 2 cups water.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour or until tender, adding water if necessary. Thicken gravy with remaining seasoned flour.

title: praline crescent dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine and brown sugar.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add sour cream and cook 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and coconut.
Stir to coat.

title: mother's noodles
directions: Beat eggs together and add water, salt and flour.
Roll paper thin and let dry.
Cut and add to broth.

title: lisa gabriel's lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to directions.
Drain well.
Heat oil in a heavy pot.
Brown beef and pork with onion and garlic, stirring often.
Grate Cheddar and Mozzarella; stir to blend. Line a 4-inch deep baking pan with layer of noodles.
Layer over noodles in order given, generous amounts of Ricotta, meat mixture, spaghetti sauce, Cheddar mixture, spaghetti sauce and Cheddar mixture.
Repeat layers until all is used, leaving sauce off last layer.
Top ingredients with generous layer of grated Parmesan and Romano cheeses.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese melts and browns lightly.
Serves 20.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Place half of the cubed bread in a 9x13 pan.
Top with cream cheese.
Add remaining bread.
Mix eggs, milk and syrup together well; pour over bread mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 loaf pans (metal pans work best). Spray pans with Pam. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes. Let cool in pans for about 10 minutes, then put them out on a cooling rack. When cool, wrap in Saran Wrap and then in aluminum foil. Keep in refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Pour corn into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup and sour cream. Spread over corn.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted butter.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat. Add tomato paste and spaghetti sauce with 1 can of water.
Spread out crescent rolls.
Add a layer of meat. Add cheese, then add rest of meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Mix all at one time except nuts and coconut; add these last. Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: snack oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil and dry dressing mix together and shake.
Pour dressing on top of crackers.
Add dill weed.
Shake well or stir several times.
Let sit overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make a ball. Roll in a mixture of an additional 1/4 cup parsley and 1/2 cup ground pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: meatballs in creamy gravy
directions: Combine ingredients except soup and noodles.
Mix well.
Shape into meatballs and brown in large skillet.
Dilute soup with equal amounts of water; add to meatballs and simmer 1/2 hour or until done, stirring frequently.
Serve over hot cooked and drained noodles.
Serves 4.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in flour, then add pecans.
Shape dough in long fingers.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: championship chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour and brown sugar; cut in cold butter until crumbly. Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips; press mixture on bottom of 13x9x2 inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, combine condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining 1 & 1/2 cups chips and nuts.
Spread evenly over baked crust. Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely. Cut into bars.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Spray (vegetable spray) 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) or 1 (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) jelly roll pan.
Heat brown sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbling around the edges. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda until foamy and light colored. Pour over popcorn and nuts in a greased, large bowl.
Stir until mixture is coated.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Slowly cook onion in butter in a saucepan until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer about 15 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 375° until golden brown.

title: baked ham and noodles
directions: In skillet, saute onion in oil.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and stir until creamy.
Add noodles, celery and ham.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and 2 tablespoons of the cocoa.
Add milk, shortening and vanilla; mix only until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour into greased shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over mixture in baking dish.
Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over the top.
(This pudding, when baked, has a chocolate sauce on bottom and cake on top.)
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with cream, if desired.

title: chocolate easter eggs
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream peanut butter and butter until well mixed.
Fold in coconut, nuts and 1 cup sugar; mix well.
Sprinkle some of the remaining sugar on a board.
Turn peanut butter mixture onto board; knead in enough of the remaining sugar until mixture holds it shape when formed.
Shape into small egg-shaped pieces.
Cover and chill for one hour.
In double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth. Dip eggs; place on waxed paper to harden.
Chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender,
Drain and chop.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil, without stirring, and add cream gradually.
Boil again.
When cool, add vanilla extract.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges.
Select a large mixing bowl and combine all ingredients with sour cream being the last.
Gently mix and chill.
Add 1/2 c. pecans, if desired.

title: crab cheese dip
directions: Place in crock-pot and heat.
Great with crackers or bread.

title: chicken with cream of chicken soup
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with pepper, thyme and soy sauce. Spray casserole dish, cover and bake 30 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and water.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in broth and enough water to cover potatoes; add chopped onions.
Cook until tender.
Mash with a little butter, leaving some potato chunks.
Add milk or half and half to thinness desired.
Add salt and pepper.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Mix flour and pepper together.
Dip chicken breast in beaten egg and then in flour and pepper mixture.
Fry over medium heat, slowly in 2 tablespoons butter and oil.
When chicken is brown, remove breasts.
Add mushrooms with 1/4 cup lemon juice and white wine. Simmer.
Use sauce to pour over chicken.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken breast in a pot with water, butter, salt and pepper.
Boil for about 45 min.
Take chicken out and add 3 cans of chicken soup.
Bring to a boil.
Pick chicken off bones and add to boiling mixture.
To make dumplings, mix flour, shortening and buttermilk.
Mix well and drop by spoon into the boiling mixture, DO NOT STIR dumplings until they are done.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: nachos dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and place ground beef between layers of paper towels.
Chop tomatoes and absorb excess liquid by placing tomatoes between layers of paper towels.
Layer the following items in a 9 x 12-inch pan in order:
bottom layer, refried beans, ground beef, salsa, tomatoes, guacamole, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and sliced olives.
You can also add sliced green onions to top for color.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan or electric skillet.
Use all the liquid on the canned beans.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 40 minutes.
Stir often.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add 2 cups flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Beat well.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup flour on apples. Fold into batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 300° in sheet pan.
Nuts are optional.
I usually add 3/4 cup chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: pecan-molasses cookies(this recipe will make your mouth water.)
directions: In a bowl, cream shortening.
Add sugar, egg and molasses. Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Stir in pecans, and mix well. Drop onto a greased cookie sheet with a teaspoon and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Make cake mix and bake in 3 round layer pans as directed. Cool.
Mix all other ingredients (except blueberries) and ice each layer alternately with blueberry filling.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to fairly hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites and salt in the meantime.
Pour syrup slowly into egg whites with mixer going at moderate speed.
Continue to beat until gloss disappears and candy is ready to drop.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: prairie hot dish
directions: Brown the meat and onion in the shortening.
Mix in salt, pepper, corn, soup, water and cheese.
Turn into 2-quart, shallow casserole.
Top with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put tablespoon of batter on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and 2/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour half of the batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Spread over cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread remaining batter (will be very thick) over top. Return to oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed until thick and lemon colored. Add butter and next 4 ingredients. Mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is set. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chili macmom
directions: Make macaroni and cheese, following directions on box.
Then mix in remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.
Great with cornbread.

title: lasagne pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Pour into large bowl.
Add tomato paste, oregano and basil.
In medium-size baking dish, layer cottage cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Mix in Mozzarella into meat mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
In large bowl mix Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Pour over meat mixture.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Serve.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into patties and fry until brown in lightly oiled skillet.
Drain on paper towels. Makes 10 to 12 salmon cakes.

title: stir-fried scallops with sesame seed
directions: Marinate scallops for 1 hour in orange and lemon juice.
Heat oil in a wok or large skillet.
Stir-fry scallions with ginger and chili for 1 minute.
Add scallops with their juice and stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sesame seed.
Add soy sauce to taste and the cornstarch mixture.
Bring to boil.
Stir in the coriander.
Serves 2 to 3 as a main course.
Serve this Oriental dish with steamed rice.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Bake and cool.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch greased, lightly floured pan.
Drain pineapple and blend remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; add soup and Cheez Whiz. Saute onions and celery in margarine. Thaw broccoli with hot water. Drain and mix broccoli with other ingredients. Put in baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet or buttered nonstick coated cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes about one pound.

title: christmas drink
directions: Beat together for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add 1 spoon of batter, 1/2 jig rum and 1 jig brandy, then hot water.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown onion and bacon together in skillet.
Transfer entire mixture to crock-pot and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix together and simmer for several hours.

title: spaghetti for 300
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer at least until dried ingredients are reconstituted.
Use 13 to 14 pounds pasta.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Put tea bags into boiling water for 3 minutes. Add sugar and stir. Add remaining ingredients and put into freezer container. Freeze solid. Take out of the freezer 10 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: traditional rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups of the flour, sugar, shortening, salt and yeast in medium bowl.
Add warm water, warm milk and egg.
Beat on low speed 1 minute, scraping bowl frequently.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead about 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place about 1 hour or until double.
Punch down.
Shape into balls (about 24) and place close together in round pan or cookie sheet.
Brush with margarine; cover and let rise about 30 minutes or until double. Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 12 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana cream surprise pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in double boiler.
Add milk and cook over hot water, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Cook 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Pour a small amount of mixture over egg yolks, beating vigorously.
Return to double boiler and cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, cool, add vanilla and chill.
Fold in whipped cream. Arrange filling and sliced bananas in layers in baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Garnish with whipped cream and banana slices.

title: easy chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put rice in bottom of casserole dish with a cover.
Put raw chicken on top.
Mix wine, water, soup and seasoning packet from rice.
Pour over top of chicken and rice.
Bake for 1 hour, covered, and for 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: sunday chicken casserole
directions: Slowly heat mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and milk together.
Remove from heat and mix in the dry onion soup mix and rice.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and place pieces of raw chicken on top. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: elegant apple cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs and flavorings.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to other mixture.
Blend well.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with combination of 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: buttermilk sky salad
directions: Bring pineapple and Jell-O to a boil until Jell-O dissolves. Cool, then add buttermilk.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into lightly oiled mold or long Pyrex dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: raisin nut spice cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift other dry ingredients, then add alternately the buttermilk and dry ingredients to the shortening mixture.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into prepared 9-inch cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and frost with White Butter Icing.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients into a large percolator.
Place brown sugar, allspice and cinnamon in percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle of electric percolator.
Yields 13 cups.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients except hot dogs.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes; add hot dogs.
The longer this cooks and sets the better the dogs.
Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: lemon sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Stir in sour cream.
Combine cake flour and soda; add 1/2 cup at a time beating constantly.
Stir in lemon juice and rind.
Turn into a well-greased and floured, 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits; mix cinnamon and sugar and roll biscuits in sugar and cinnamon and place into greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and honey and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from pan when done.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Put in container and refrigerate.
Just before ready to serve, toss all together.
This does not do well the next day, so mix only what you think you will eat at that time.

title: creole pralines
directions: Combine sugar, water and vinegar.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add butter and nuts.
Remove from heat.
Beat until it starts to get thick.
Drop onto waxed paper using teaspoon.
Cool.
Makes 3 dozen pralines.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix all and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: irish-italian spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger lightly, adding salt and onion.
Drain grease, add other ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Pour sauce over spaghetti to serve.
Can be topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Add margarine or butter.
Chop pecans very fine.
Add to mixture.
Make 3 logs and roll in wax paper. Refrigerate until cold and set enough to cut.
Place cut cookie dough on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown or overcook.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples and mash.
Add other ingredients and cook 24 hours in crock-pot.

title: worcestershire onions
directions: Cut onion 4 ways halfway down.
Put 1/2 stick margarine in cut.
Cover in Worcestershire sauce and place in foil.
Cook on grill or in oven until tender.
(May also be cooked in microwave in microwave dish.)

title: chewy squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Gradually add vanilla.
Mix flour well with other mixture.
Add salt and nuts. Mix well.
Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a medium bowl; mix well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead dough 3 or 4 times.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix 1/2 of Cool Whip
and all the pistachio pudding in a bowl. Add fruits and mix again.
Top with Cool Whip when served.

title: my favorite pie crust
directions: Mix thoroughly.
This will make approximately 24 single pie crusts.
Freezes wonderful.

title: diane's country corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter in small skillet over medium-high heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and stir constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Remove from heat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix everything together with mixer.
Buy graham cracker crusts. Makes 2 pies.
Keep frozen until ready to eat.

title: ginger ale punch
directions: Mix jello and 9 cups of water together; bring to a boil.
Mix 4 cups of sugar and 4 cups of water; bring to a boil.
Combine jello mixture and sugar mixture; let cool.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice; freeze until hard.
Remove 2 hours before serving.
Add the chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Stir well.
Makes enough liquid for 2 punch bowls.

title: riddle chili
directions: Cook hamburger to well done.
Drain grease until all is gone. Next, add chopped onion; after onion is done in ground beef, cook spaghetti in large pan of boiling water until done.
Add beans, tomato puree and whole tomatoes to meat.
Add chili powder, garlic salt and pepper as ingredients cook.
Add spaghetti.
If you like hot chili, add three chopped jalapeno peppers.
Cook ingredients together for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and beat until oranges are small specks.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: heart linzer tarts
directions: Combine flour, confectioners sugar and salt.
Add butter.
Use mixer and process with on/off turns until mixture is like coarse meal.
Process until dough pulls away from bowl and forms a ball. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 325°. On well-floured surface, roll out half the dough 1/8-inch thick. Cut dough in heart shapes with 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Place cookies on baking sheet.
Using a 1-inch heart cutter, cut out centers of half the cookies.
Place centers on baking sheet.
Bake 13 to 16 minutes for large cookies, 10 minutes for small cookies, until lightly browned.
Remove from sheet and cool on rack.
Spread each large solid cookie with 1/2 to 1 teaspoon jam.
Sift confectioners sugar (or dunk) over heart shaped ring cookies and place on jam topped cookies.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Boil sugar and syrup 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and cornflakes.
Stir fast!
Pour in buttered cake pan. Cool and cut.

title: veal or chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cut ham and cheese into strips.
Lay cutlets on table.
Put a strip of ham and cheese on each cutlet, then roll tight.
Add a toothpick to hold together, if necessary.
Use three bowls, one for flour, one for bread crumbs and one for eggs.
Roll meat in flour, then in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Put a little oil in a frying pan and fry rolled meat until brown.
Place sauteed meat rolls in a roasting pan and cook in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix each package of Kool-Aid as package directions indicate. Then mix with other ingredients.
Sweeten to taste.

title: angel food cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Set tube pan in oven and heat.
Sift together flour and confectioners sugar. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Add white sugar, a little at a time.
Beat until egg whites form stiff peaks. Add flavoring. Add flour and white sugar mixture, 1/4 at a time.
Put in pan. Shake down to get rid of air bubbles. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Take from oven. Turn upside down until completely cool.
Run knife around sides of pan and take out.

title: pasties
directions: Peel and cut in small pieces the potatoes and onion.
Mix in a large bowl with ground beef, broken into pieces.
Salt and pepper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all three bags of frozen vegetables.
Boil until soft. Add eggs, flour, cottage cheese and shredded cheese.
Mix all together in baking dish.
Melt stick of butter in baking dish first.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Blend together with a pastry blender (as for making pie dough) the butter, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Work until crumbly, then pack closely over the apples.
If the apples are very dry, a little water may be placed in the bottom of the pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put orange juice and grated rind into a large measuring cup.
Add shortening.
Then pour boiling water up to the 3/4 mark in the measuring cup.
Lightly beat 1 egg and add to dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients and stir.
Mix in cranberries and nuts.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Generously grease casserole dish and pour chicken broth in bottom of dish.
Crush chips and layer over broth.
Dice chicken and layer over chips.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion. Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave; add 2 cans Hy-Power chili to cheese and heat.
Add tomato juice and Worcestershire sauce to taste. Combine with hamburger in crock-pot and serve with chips.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until wafer crumbs are moist.
Butter a loaf pan and pack mixture in.
Place in refrigerator and let set overnight until firm.
Turn fruit cake out on plate.
Keep covered in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add mixture of flour, soda and salt gradually.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread in greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cheese and potato soup
directions: Put potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in water; cook. Add chicken
broth.
Thicken
with
cornstarch.
Add
Velveeta cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Makes about 1/2 gallon.

title: vienna bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup margarine at room temperature and 1/2 cup sugar.
Work until creamy and mixed well.
Beat in the salt and egg yolks.
Add flour and knead with fingers until smooth.
Pat dough evenly into a 12 x 17-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in pan in heated 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil one minute.
Turn heat off.
Immediately add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until peanut butter has melted. Add oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: stir-fry(stir-fried beef and peppers)
directions: Prepare rice as label directs.
Cut round steak lengthwise in half, then cut diagonally into paper thin slices.
In medium bowl, mix soy sauce and the next four ingredients; add beef and toss lightly to coat.
Set aside.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Shred chicken and set aside.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add chicken, salsa, cream cheese and 3 cups cheddar cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add a little chicken broth if it is too dry. Spoon into flour tortillas and place in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with more salsa and 1 cup of shedded cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, 2 cups sugar, applesauce, eggs, orange juice, salt and vanilla.
Beat until combined.
Use another bowl, toss apples with cinnamon and rest of sugar.
Use a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Spread 1/3 of batter.
Cover with 1/2 of apples. Repeat layers.
Spoon remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Let cool in pan 20 minutes before removing from pan.
Just before serving, dust with confectioners sugar (optional).

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add sugar. Stir in lemonade and cold water.
Add pineapple juice.
Pour into container and freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before needed.
Add ginger ale and mix in punch bowl.
Makes 4 quarts or 64 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender.
Drain. Place layer of noodles in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, buttered.
Top with layer of meat sauce, half the cheeses, remaining noodles, remaining meat sauce and cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in graham cracker crust or baked pie shell.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts on top.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: okra patties
directions: Mix okra, onion, salt, pepper, water, and egg. In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, and corn meal; add to okra mixture. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Cook over medium heat until brown. Remove from oil and let drain. Serve and enjoy!

title: cactus cones
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, milk, rice, green pepper, 2 teaspoons taco or enchilada mix and salt.
Shape meat mixture into 8 cones.
Brown cones on all sides in cooking fat.
Combine tomatoes, tomato juice and remaining enchilada sauce mix in deep pan.
Bring to a boil.
Place cones (pointing up) in sauce.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cones to warm serving dish.
Thicken sauce with flour, if desired, and spoon over cones. Makes 8 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread into a greased pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes longer.

title: hopscotch crunchies
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter over hot (not boiling) water. Remove from heat.
Stir.
Stir in noodles and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill till set.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Do not use directions on cake mix.
Mix eggs, oil and oranges with juice together.
Beat 2 minutes into cake mix.
Bake in a tube of Bundt pan at 350° until done.

title: christmas odor punch(not for consumption)
directions: Boil in large kettle several minutes.
Lower heat and let it simmer, allowing room to fill with the Christmas aroma.
You may add water and stir occasionally.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Flour pork chops; brown in oil.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon fat; add soup, 1 soup can water and rice.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add water as needed.

title: chewy cake
directions: Put first 3 ingredients into double boiler and stir while melting.
Let it get warm, do not let it boil, then add flour, vanilla, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy coconut pie
directions: Cover an unbaked 9-inch crust with coconut.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out of pie clean.
The coconut will rise to the top of the pie.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in butter or oil.
Spread rice in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice, reserving 1 tablespoon drained mushrooms (reserving juice). Spread the mushrooms over rice.

title: stuffing mix
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients.
Store in covered container.
To prepare, combine 1/4 cup of the above mixture and 1 3/4 cups water.
Add 1/4 cup butter or oleo, melted.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat; cover and simmer 6 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups crumbled bread.
Stir to moisten.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand several minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: slush
directions: Steep tea in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Stir sugar in cold water to dissolve.
Add orange juice, lemonade and vodka.
Freeze 24 hours.
Use with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Add bananas, pineapple, blackberries and nuts to jello.
Chill until set.
Beat sour cream, cream cheese and sugar together until fluffy.
Spread on top of jello.
Cool Whip may be used for top if preferred.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Put in pan and	sprinkle
with brown sugar and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar well.
Add vanilla and flour; cream well.
Add crushed potato chips.
Drop by teaspoons on an ungreased cookie sheet until all batter is used.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool; then dust with powdered sugar. Do not cover because they will become soggy.

title: dilled oyster crackers
directions: Mix dressing mix, garlic powder, dill weed, lemon pepper and oil.
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in a warm 250° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir halfway through baking time.
Store in airtight container when cool.

title: lemon lush
directions: In another bowl, mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Spread this mixture on top of cooled mixture.
Next, spread lemon pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with Cool Whip, if you like.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into bowl. Stir in oats.
Add remaining ingredients; stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased medium-sized muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated hot oven (425°) about 15 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat oleo, sifted sugar, vanilla and eggs for 15 minutes on high speed.
Pour over crust.
Layer bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip and cherries on top.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package.
Drain and rinse pasta with cold water and place in a large mixing bowl that has a seal tight lid.
Add all vegetables to pasta and toss together.
Pour Italian dressing over mixture and refrigerate until serving.

title: doris' dessert bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread in greased pan. Top with the mixture of cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and salt.
Knead until smooth.
Roll into balls and dip in chocolate or can be used as center for peanut butter cups.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and form into balls.
Arrange in baking dish in single layer.
Brown in oven 15 minutes at 370°. Mix the soup with the water and flour.
Pour soup mixture over meatballs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.
I turn meatballs once. Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Place chicken pieces in a casserole dish; salt and pepper.
In pan or microwave dish, melt butter and add flour and paprika.
Mix well, then brush over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Mix soup and milk and pour around and over chicken; bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued ham
directions: Mix the brown sugar with the water. Simmer until the sugar dissolves. Add the chili sauce and mustard and simmer for 5 minutes. Add ham and simmer, or put in crock pot on low. Serve on sandwich rolls.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl. Stir well and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients, except lettuce, in a medium bowl. Add cream cheese mixture to apple mixture. Toss gently. Cover and chill. Toss again before serving. Serve in lettuce-lined bowl. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Serve on crisp greens, top with your favorite dressing.

title: stephen skinner's favorite fluffy meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Pat into loaf shape; top with 3 tablespoons catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip(serves 6)
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning.
Spread into bottom of an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in the same order as above.
Preparation Time:
40 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal sheet cake
directions: After oatmeal sets mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Oil and flour sheet pan.
Pour cake mix in and bake at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: ice cream pancakes
directions: Mix and whip until fluffy.
Grease 12-inch frying pan or griddle and place over medium heat.
Pour 3 or 4 pancakes at a time into pan.
Cook until bubbles form and edges are dry, turn and cook until golden brown.
Have syrup and butter ready and serve immediately with milk, orange juice or coffee.
Makes 12 to 14 pancakes.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients; chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Chop onions and peppers.
Combine dry ingredients in a bowl. Add beaten egg, butter, milk, onions and peppers.
Deep fry by the spoonful.
Cook until golden brown.

title: mexican pan dulce(mexican sweet buns)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the water.
Sift flour again with the sugar and salt into bowl.
Add the yeast, butter and eggs; beat until smooth.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place until
doubled in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch it down; turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Pinch off pieces of dough and shape into smooth rounded balls about 1 1/4 inches in diameter.
Place balls of dough on a greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
With the palm of your hand, press each ball down to flatten it slightly. Gently spread about 1 tablespoon topping on each bun and then let buns rise until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm. Makes about 18.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drizzle oil over.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and pepper.
Toss gently to coat.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender when pierced with fork.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onions and cook 12 to 15 minutes or until tender and transparent. Saving some for topping. Sprinkle cracker crumbs in a greased 9x13 inch casserole dish to line bottom and sides.
Layer cooked onions, soup and cheese in dish.
Lightly season onion layer with salt. Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper
and pour over layers.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs and extra cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Serves 6-8.

title: one - step lasagna
