directions: Combine beef into 2 quart microproof casserole. Place in microwave oven; cook on high, (100%) for 3 minutes. Pause and stir to break up beef; cook on high, (100%) for 2 minutes. Pause and remove from oven; stir; drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce, water and salt. Spread 1/3 of the beef mixture in 11 x 7-inch microproof baking dish. Arrange half of the noodles over sauce. Spread with 1 cup ricotta cheese. Sprinkle with 1 cup mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers once. Top with remaining beef mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Double wrap with plastic wrap and place in oven. Cook on simmer/low heat, (50%) for 30 minutes. Pause and sprinkle with remaining 1 cup mozzarella cheese. Do not cover. Cook on medium heat, (70%) for 2 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley and serve with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Cook first four ingredients for 15 minutes; add jello. Cool. This can be frozen.

title: green garden salad
directions: Dice up all vegetable ingredients into small bits.
Mix in cottage cheese, mayonnaise and white pepper.
Put in the fridge for about 1 or 2 hours.
Serve on a leaf of lettuce.

title: creamy peach double decker
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and chill until thickened. Fold peaches
into	half
of
the Jell-O and spoon into mold or pan.
Chill
until	set,
not
firm, about 10 minutes. Blend whipped topping
into
remaining
Jell-O
and spoon over clear layer.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Makes 5 cups.

title: swedish pancakes(plattar och pannkakor)
directions: Beat together the flour and half of the milk, or the water, to a smooth batter.
Add the eggs, remaining milk or cream, salt and melted margarine.
Beat until well blended.
Cook the pancakes on a hot skillet.
If desired, make a pancake tarta by stacking the pancakes with applesauce or other fruit preserves between the layers.
Let cool and spread the top with whipped cream.
Serve cut in wedges.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 170°.
Grease a tube pan with butter.
Cut dough into small pieces and dip in butter, then roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Arrange evenly in the tube pan.
Place in a 170° oven for 1 1/2 hours until doubled.
Take pan out of oven and heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Take out of pan while hot.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: In heavy frypan, brown ribs in 3 to 4 tablespoons shortening. (Cast-iron Dutch oven is excellent.)
Put all other ingredients in 2-quart pan and bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally. Place all ribs in frypan and cover with sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until tender; baste occasionally.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bring syrup, sugar and margarine to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour half into large shallow baking dish. Add potatoes. Top with remaining syrup. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake in a 350° to 400° oven, basting often for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: bermuda banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and bake in a preheated moderate oven (250°) for forty plus minutes.
Use a nonstick pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth.
Put meat mixture into medium loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: strawberry banana jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups of boiling water.
Cool until just lukewarm.
Add frozen strawberries to Jell-O and break apart frozen berries.
Jell-O should be cool at this point.
Add mashed bananas and pineapple to Jell-O mixture.
Pour half of Jell-O into a 9 x 13-inch pan; let set up.
Spread the sour cream over the set up Jell-O.
Slowly pour other half of Jell-O mixture over the sour cream and let set.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 hours.
Serve with chips.
May be used as topping on hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, sugar and cinnamon.
Add oil and buttermilk; mix well.
Stir in eggs, nuts and apricots.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Cream together all ingredients, except wraps, meat and oil. Fold in meat.
Place mixture in center of each wrap and pinch to close.
Fry at 375° in hot oil until golden brown.
Do not overcook.

title: snicker bar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar, butter and peanut butter. Add vanilla and beaten eggs; mix.
Add baking soda, baking powder and flour; mix well.
Cut Fun Size Snickers in half.
Wrap dough around each 1/2 bar, forming a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cookies will flatten as they bake with candy bars as center filling.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until light brown.

title: coconut cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease and flour 12 cup fluted pan or 10-inch angel food tube pan.
In large bowl, combine all cake ingredients except coconut; beat 2 minutes at low speed, then beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Fold in coconut; pour into prepared pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan 25 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: cheese cake
directions: Bat together until smooth and fluffy.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes in graham pie shell.
Garnish with pie filling.

title: chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in flat casserole and top with cheese.
Over this, pour soup and wine that have been mixed together.
Take seasoning packet from stuffing mix and sprinkle over soup mixture. Cover this with dry stuffing mix.
Pour melted butter over this. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Set aside.
Add oil and vanilla to eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Add zucchini and stir until blended.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 2 loaves.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cover chicken with water; add salt, bay leaves and onions. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours; skim off top.
Remove chicken from stock; discard skin and bones and bay leaves.
Chop meat and return to stock.
Bring to boil; add saffron and noodles and cook at medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Pour into casserole dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
After all is in dish, sprinkle chips over top of casserole and bake for 30 minutes.

title: beef and potato stew
directions: Cook beef cubes until they begin to stick and are tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Melt butter and add sugar; stir and cook over low heat for a few minutes. Add about a tablespoon of water, then pineapple with juice. Dissolve cornstarch in a little water and add to the mixture. Stir in lemon juice. Cut toast into small cubes and add. Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix well.
Fold in 1 small Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make dough stiff enough to be rolled out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake on cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Add the garlic powder and chili powder.
Drain.
Put meat mixture in crock-pot and add the remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Just before serving, add the cheese.
Stir and serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix the ingredients with mixer on medium speed until blended and at high speed until smooth and creamy.

title: party pizza
directions: Cook hamburger meat and sausage.
Drain well.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add spice ingredients.
Spread on bread slices.
Top with olive slice, if desired.
Serve warm.

title: easy barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until completely cooked.
Add condensed tomato soup.
Stir well and simmer for 30 minutes or until thick.
Serve on buns.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add water and all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer (covered) for about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove leaves.
Freezes well.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: swiss-broccoli quiche
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 8 servings.

title: curried haddock chowder
directions: Heat oil and cook onion and bacon for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add green pepper and curry and cook a further minute.
Pour over stock and milk, then add fish, corn and potatoes.
Season.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: german-russian greble
directions: Beat eggs;
add
soda to sour cream and blend together. Sift rest
of
dry ingredients.	Add to egg and cream mixture. Melt butter
and
add
to
mixture.
Mix
until creamy smooth. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Pour enough milk into dry ingredients to set.
Stir, making a paste.
Once all ingredients have been mixed well, then add remaining milk.
Put over low heat and cook, stirring constantly.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks well, then add a small amount of hot mixture to the egg yolks. Mix well.
Add egg mixture to rest of pie ingredients and continue to cook over low heat until pie mixture is thickened to your liking.
Add vanilla at the end.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shell.
Use egg whites to make meringue for top of pie.
Brown in oven.

title: cinnamon ornaments(do not eat)
directions: Mix applesauce and cinnamon until well blended.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick; use cutters to make shapes for any holiday.
Use straw to put a hole through top of ornament.
Let dry for several days; carefully turning occasionally.
Makes approximately 12 ornaments.
Put ribbon or yarn through hole and hang.
Great for the tree or on the wreath.
They make great fresheners for the bathroom too.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender and add 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
Finish cooking until done.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch, mixed with 1/4 cup water; stir into carrots.

title: miniature cheese cupcakes
directions: Place vanilla wafers into foil cupcake cups.
Beat the remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour in cups.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve warm or chilled.
May also add chopped onion, olives, etc.

title: upside-down carrot cake
directions: Prepare 2 round cake pans with the butter or 50/50 butter and oil mixture (I use expeller pressed canola or sesame oil).
Coat bottom and sides of pan.
Add 3 to 6 tablespoons brown sugar, spreading evenly.
Press walnuts or pecans into sugar, covering the bottom of pan with nuts.
About 5 minutes before filling the pan with batter, warm the pans in a 350°, preheated oven.

title: bizcochitos
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugar gradually, then eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
In another bowl sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add enough wine to make dough stick together.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut into cookies.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: steamed turkey sausage and cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot with lid.
Bring to boil for steaming and cover.
Turn heat down; steam for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally during steaming.
Serve on white rice.

title: microwave cheese sticks
directions: Cream butter and cheese with mixer.
Mix in flour, salt and pepper sauce until mixture resembles soft cookie dough.
Turn mixture out on floured board.
Sprinkle with flour; roll out to 1/8 inch thickness, flouring lightly as needed.
Cut into strips 1/2 inch wide and 2 1/3 inches long.
Line microwave baking sheet or 12 x 12-inch sheet of cardboard with waxed paper.
Place cheese sticks on paper.
Elevate baking sheet on roasting rack.
Microwave at High for 3 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and thoroughly drain spinach in colander, mashing down with spoon to extract liquid.
Mix together flour, butter, salt, and eggs until a paste-like mixture forms.
Add all ingredients to a 5 qt. crockpot and cook on low for 5 hours.
Stir occasionally. Salt a pinch if desired.

title: honey orange yams
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat the margarine, honey, orange rind, orange juice and salt.
Boil gently for 10 minutes.
Add yams. Continue boiling gently, turning yams once midway until most of the syrup is absorbed and the yams are hot, about 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill baked and cooled pie shells with fresh strawberries.
(If strawberries are very large, they may be sliced.)
Cook sugar, cornstarch, jello, water and food coloring until thick.
Cool and pour over strawberries.
When set, top with Cool Whip.
Delicious!

title: poor boy stew
directions: Brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Use
3	tablespoons canning/pickling salt
for	each
5 pounds shredded cabbage.
(Add 1 teaspoon of sugar for each
5 pounds
of cabbage
if cabbage isn't	mature.)
Mix
shredded cabbage
with salt and sugar.
Pack into	stone
jar
tightly. Let brine form. If more brine is needed, make more by boiling 2 tablespoons salt and 1 quart water together,
and then cool. Set stone jar on rack to allow circulation.
Cover
kraut with glass plate and weigh the plate down with a jar of water heavy enough so brine covers cabbage.
Drape a white
cloth over top of stone jar.

title: pesto gorgonzola torte
directions: Cream the gorgonzola, cream cheese, asiago and pesto until smooth.
Mix together the sun-dried tomatoes and basil.
Line 6 one-pint containers with plastic wrap and spray with Pam release. Put 1 tablespoon pine nuts in the bottom, then a large pinch of parsley and 2/3 cup cheese mixture.
Divide the tomato/basil mixture among the 6 containers and top this off with remaining cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate until firm.

title: rosemary turkey pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid. In medium skillet, combine reserved liquid, turkey and rosemary. Cook 5 minutes or until liquid evaporates. Place pizza crust on baking sheet. Chop tomatoes; spread evenly over crust. Cover with half of the cheese. Top with turkey mixture, pepper slices and green onions. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake for 10 minutes in 450° oven or until cheese is hot and bubbly. Good use of leftover turkey. Children love it!

title: reunion casserole
directions: Prepare cheese dinner according to directions except add undiluted mushroom soup; set aside.
Saute hamburger, onions and peppers, season to taste.
Cook until meat is done.
Add macaroni and cheese dinner.
Stir well.
Put in casserole dish; top with shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Beat eggs until well blended.
Beat in sour cream and salt. Stir in onion, cheese and spinach (press out liquid in spinach). Pour into an unbaked 8-inch pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar; then mix together with sweet potatoes, melted butter and vanilla.

title: porcupine beef balls
directions: Rinse rice in cold water.
In large bowl, mix beef and rice (use your hands).
Form into balls (should make about 9).
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour tomato sauce over them.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken parmesan pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pizza crust on 10-inch pizza pan as directed on package.
Set aside.
In medium size bowl, combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt and Italian seasoning.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine, then in cracker crumb mixture and place individually on a large baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Spread tomato sauce evenly over prepared pizza crust.
Arrange baked chicken pieces evenly on tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until crust is golden and cheese is bubbly.
Slice and serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Sift dry ingredients
and add to mixture.
Roll out.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's; reserve remaining for decoration.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Add eggs; beat until combined.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla; beat well.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes; reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until set.

title: midge's vegetable sandwiches
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in blender and grind.
Drain.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Chill overnight.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and Dream Whip together.
Put in baked pie shell.
Chill.
Put canned blueberry filling on top of cream. Chill then serve.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup together in boiler.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and then corn flakes. Drop onto wax paper.

title: aunt sue's cheesecake
directions: Press onto side and bottom of spring-form pan.

title: sweet potato casserolegroves, texas
directions: Beat well and pour mixture in glass pan.

title: ham loaf
directions: Have butcher grind and mix the ham, pork and beef.
Mix in eggs, bread crumbs and milk.
Baste every 20 minutes with syrup of remaining ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.
Serve with Mustard Sauce.
Makes 3 to 4 loaves.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients and cut in Crisco until mixed thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Mix well.
Roll on floured board and cut as for biscuits. Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.
You may cook small amount and store unused dough in refrigerator in a covered bowl.
Will keep two weeks or more.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan until thickened for about 10 minutes.
Use over pork and rice.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain; rinse away fat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve topped with Fritos and grated cheese.

title: glazed pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in water and lime overnight.
Rinse well.
Then soak in cold water for 2 hours, then rinse and put in ice for 1 hour.
Make your syrup with sugar, salt, vinegar, pickling spice and add ginger right before the cucumbers.
When syrup is boiling, add cucumbers and boil for 20 minutes, then simmer for 1 hour. Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a lightly greased casserole all ingredients.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Sprinkle nuts on top and chill.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Start with plenty of patience.
Add one large hug.
A lap or arm around the shoulders is best added at this time.
Gently stir in a bit of understanding.
Blend well.
Continue adding understanding until the right temperament is reached.
Check for tears or frowns; add more understanding.
When no tears or frowns remain, top with a handful of encouragement.
Garnish with a generous sprinkle of humor.

title: halloween bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and melt in oven.
Remove from oven and distribute evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk evenly over the crumbs. Top with chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: spiced pumpkin rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in warm water in a large bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining sugar, pumpkin and next 3 ingredients.
Gradually stir in 3 3/4 cups bread flour and wheat flour to make a soft dough.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons bread flour evenly over work surface.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes).
Place dough in a large bowl coated with vegetable cooking spray, turning to coat top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts until dough is doubled in bulk.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly with electric mixer.
Chill.
Set out before serving.
Best at room temperature.
Serve with assorted bread or crackers.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Let ice cream and Cool Whip soften. Crumble up Oreos in big bowl. Add the ice cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well and freeze overnight on a cookie sheet.

title: broccoli salad
directions: For a large group can add some lettuce (1/2 head).

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large mixing bowl combine oil and sugar. Add eggs and bananas. Mix well; add flour, baking powder. Mix well; add milk, vanilla, and walnuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes. Lightly cover the tops of the loaves with foil if the tops begin turning too brown before the bread is done. Bread is done when toothpick is inserted in enter comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add mashed bananas, vanilla and sour cream. Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Fold into the creamed mixture, stirring just to blend.
Spoon into one 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan or two 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, depending on size of pan at 350°.

title: sweet spice cake lotte
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add the flour, baking powder, milk, cocoa, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt to the butter mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and gently fold into the cake mixture.
Pour into a well buttered large cookie sheet or round spring-form pan.
Bake in a 200° C (390° F) oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients, except last three.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle evenly with yellow cake mix, sifted over pie mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients to soft ball state, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and marshmallows.
By the time this melts, it is ready to pour in pan.

title: jenifer house country store ginger-molasses cookie recipe
directions: Cream the butter, molasses, water, salt and brown sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and then add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Roll in balls (2-inches in diameter).
Roll in granulated sugar. Bake for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Yields approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: macaroni toss
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Thaw peas and cook if desired. Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Microwave onions and celery until tender.
Cook rice.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix onions and celery, rice and broccoli.
Add cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soups.
Stir.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir well.
Heat through in microwave or in oven.

title: feta cheese chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts to about 5 x 5-inches.
Place Feta cheese in center and roll up, tucking in sides.
Combine crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then roll in crumbs.
Place in shallow pan and pour remaining butter over breasts.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Mix egg, milk and oil together.
Pour liquid in middle; stir just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans while still warm.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into cubes.
Add tomatoes to raw eggplant and cook slowly in saucepan until tender.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients using enough crackers to take up moisture.
Bake in large casserole in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut wing tips off at joint and discard.
Cut each wing in half at joint.
On rack in broiler pan, arrange wings.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 25 minutes or until brown, turning occasionally. Transfer to serving dish.
In small saucepan over medium heat, heat Tabasco sauce, butter and vinegar.
Drizzle evenly over wings.
Serve with celery sticks and dressing for dipping.

title: fruit roll
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well. Use your hands to blend. Divide into 3 equal parts. Roll each into a log 2-inches in diameter. Roll each log in powdered sugar. Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight; cut into slices.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift together and fold in flour, salt and soda.
Add vanilla.
Blend and add pecans and apples. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes in a 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan.
Leave in pan.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine water, vinegar and beaten egg.
Mix and chill 15 minutes.
Roll in pie pan.

title: mock lemon pie (rhubarb)
directions: Cut up and measure rhubarb.
Add 1 cup of water and boil until rhubarb can be well blended by whipping.
Make pie shell and put in oven.

title: beef crock-pot appetizer
directions: Brown beef and drain
off fat.	Put beef and all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook
for 1 hour.
Keep in crock-pot for informal parties.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with nacho chips. (Great for parties.)

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; remove fat.
Boil noodles as directed.
Mix together sauce, oregano and meat.
Layer as follows: Layer of meat mixture, layer of noodles, layer of cottage cheese, layer of Mozzarella cheese and layer of meat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8 x 8-inch dish.
Mix other ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: diabetic molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out 1/8 inch thick and cut with 2 or 3 inch cookie cutters.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: stickies
directions: Roll pastry very thin, about 12-inch square.
Make a paste of sugars, butter and vanilla.
Spread onto pastry evenly.
Roll as a jelly roll.
Next, slice and arrange in a close circle in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and sour cream. Fold in coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.
Done when wooden pick comes out clean.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Cream part of cocoa-sugar mixture with the butter.
Blend in milk,
vanilla and lemon extract.
Add remaining cocoa-sugar mixture and beat well to desired spreading consistency.
More milk may be added if needed.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pie pan.
Beat the powdered sugar, flavoring and softened butter for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, beating one at a time. Spread over crumbs.
Slice and layer bananas.
Drain pineapple and cover bananas.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and lightly swirl chocolate syrup.
Cover with Cool Whip, then top with pecans and cherries.

title: rice chex s'mores
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together.
Remove from heat; add Rice Chex and stir gently.
Add chocolate chips; stir gently.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: lemon dinner rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast and salt.
Add 2 1/2 cups very warm water. Add flour, one cup at a time.
Let rise 1 hour or more.
Flour a countertop well.
Take out a large handful of dough and pat out to 1/2-inch thick.
Do this 4 or 5 times.
Each time cut out with a biscuit cutter and put on sprayed cookie sheets, almost touching. Let rise another hour or more.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Pour into heated and greased large iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually add well drained pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion, and garlic salt.
Chill well. Form into one large or two small balls and roll in one cup chopped pecans.
Garnish with fresh parsley and twisted pineapple slices centered with a cherry.

title: all occasion punch
directions: In large bowl, combine Jell-O and 2 cups of hot water; dissolve.
Then add 2 or 3 cups of sugar.
Add 8 cups of cold water, pineapple juice and lemonade.
Mix well, divide into 3 equal parts and freeze.
Remove from freezer one hour before serving, chop up and add ginger ale.
Serves about 35.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Yields 20 servings (1 punch bowl).
For 40 people, make 2 bowls.

title: oven-barbecued chicken
directions: You will also need vegetable oil spray.
Do not use vegetable oil spray near an open flame or a heat source.
Read and follow directions on can before using.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown crumbled beef; saute the onion and green pepper with the seasonings in a large skillet until the beef is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes and rice, stirring frequently.
When mixture is combined, spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream margarine; add eggs, then add sugar, flour, nuts and vanilla.
Batter will be very thick.
Bake in large pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix soda with flour.
Melt chocolate bars in syrup over low heat; cool.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add cooled chocolate, then flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in a lightly greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: "nita's onions"
directions: Use large flat sweet Texas onions.
Try to get flat ones, the sweet Texas onions.
Having sweet onions is important or any onions not too "hot" and bitter.
Slice them.
Separate the slices and store in refrigerator in plastic bag until just before serving time.
Slice them almost 1-inch deep.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add vanilla and flavoring.
Bake in tube pan.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening until lightly fluffy.
Beat in molasses and beaten egg; sift in flour, baking soda, ginger and salt.
Chill 2 hours.
Divide dough into fourths.
Roll out to your thickness; cut with cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Wash chicken; drain.
Shake in mixture of flour, salt and pepper in paper bag to coat.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll chicken pieces, one at a time, in melted margarine to coat all over.
Place, skin side down in single layer, in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons margarine in saucepan.
Stir in honey, lemon juice and soy sauce; mix well.
After the 30 minutes, turn chicken.
Pour honey mixture over it.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Baste several times.
Serves 4.

title: grandma jojo's barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in container with tight lid.
Shake together.
Brush on chicken, etc.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Mix garlic salt and pepper into beaten eggs.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Put margarine in dish.
Put casserole dish in 250° oven until margarine melts.
Roll chicken in egg mixture, then roll in crackers and roll in butter in casserole dish.
Place chicken, bone side down, in dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 200° for 2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together crumbs and 1 stick butter (melted).
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan and press in.
Chill.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cook 1/4 cup sugar, 4 cups rhubarb and 1/4 cup water until tender.
Add 2 packages strawberry Jell-O; mix well.
Add 3 cups marshmallows.
When very cool, fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Line unbaked pie shell with foil.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes. Remove foil.
Bake for 4 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.
Saute mushrooms and onion for 5 minutes; drain.

title: grannie greene's iron skillet apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients well and pour into greased iron skillet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
May be served with ice cream.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain grease.
Cook 2 cups rice in water until done.
Put hamburger, sausage, rice, seasoning salt, garlic powder, diced onion, diced tomatoes and bell pepper pieces in pan and blend and cook until done.
Fill whole bell peppers and freeze.
Pull one at a time from freezer.
Cook in microwave 5 minutes.

title: skyline chili(cincinnati chili)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot and simmer for 3 hours, skimming off grease as it forms.
Spread over spaghetti; top with shredded Colby or Cheddar cheese, onions, kidney beans and oyster crackers.
Choose the toppings you like!

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Mix Jell-O with blueberry pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until jelled.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt cream cheese, Cheddar and margarine until smooth.
Fold small amount of hot cheese into egg whites.
Fold into remaining cheese mixture.
Spear cube of bread and dip, coating all sides. Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or freeze (can freeze 2 months).
Put in bag after frozen.
Uncover.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all together; form into balls and roll in flour.
Brown in small amount of shortening.
Place in baking pan and pour over them 1 can tomato soup and 1 can water, mixed.
Cover and bake at 300° for
2 hours.
Add more water at end of first hour if needed.

title: walk to school cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into 2 rolls.
Chill about 2 hours in refrigerator.
Slice and put on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Put cubed bread in bottom of casserole dish; put sausage over bread crumbs (use 2-quart dish).
Pour egg and milk mixture over this and top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken rice goodness
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions; drain.
Arrange in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the shredded American cheese; top with chicken.
Spoon on cooked rice; season with salt and pepper.

title: a.m. delight muffins
directions: Bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes. 1 1/2 dozen.
(Very Good.)

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Take meat off boiled chicken and cut up when cool. Take skin off, if desired. Combine seeds, crackers and butter. Put layer of this on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Mix chicken pieces, soup and sour cream. Layer in casserole dish. Put another layer of cracker crust mixture on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered. Makes one large or 2 to 3 small casseroles. May be made and frozen before cooking.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onions, garlic, mushrooms and carrots in olive oil.
Add the tomato, water and spices; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer and add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked ham with orange-mustard glaze
directions: Heat oven to 325 degrees.
Place ham, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Pour water into pan.
Bake for 1 hour. Remove ham from oven.
Add sherry or orange juice to roasting pan.
If necessary, trim fat from ham.
Score ham diagonally in 1-inch intervals, cutting about 1/4 inch deep; score in opposite direction to form diamond shapes.
In a small bowl, combine marmalade and mustards; mix well.
Brush half of the marmalade mixture over ham; baste with pan juices. Return to oven; bake 1 to 1-1/2 hours more, basting frequently with pan juices and brushing with remaining marmalade mixture.
Let ham stand in roasting pan for 15 minutes before slicing, basting frequently with pan juices. For the mustard, I use Denison mustard but any with the seeds in it will work.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients in pie plate. Mix with fork.
Press out with fingers.

title: lou's wassail
directions: Make a spice bag with the spices and place the bag in the juices.
Bring mixture to a boil; remove from heat.
Store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Heat and remove spice bag. This is very tart.

title: zucchini squash boats
directions: Cook squash whole in boiling water until barely tender (7 to 10 minutes).
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop squash out of shells and mash.
Cook sausage with onion and drain off fat.
Stir with mashed squash.
Reserve 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spoon into shells.
Place in shallow baking dish and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops with garlic powder, pepper and salt.
Brown pork in 2 tablespoons hot oil.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Mix in order given.
Spread in pan about 14 x 8-inch, lined with wax paper.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in moderate oven at 350°. Cut in finger-shaped pieces and roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until light.
Then add oil and beat.
Add 1/2 of dry ingredients and beat well.
Remove beaters.
The rest must be hand mixed with a wooden spoon.
Add zucchini and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 1-pound bread pans that are greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Stir in butter, Parmesan and beaten eggs
to form crust.
Layer in shallow casserole dish. Cook, uncovered,
in microwave for 2 minutes.
Spread Ricotta cheese
on crust.
Cook all remaining ingredients together to make
filling. Pour over crust and cook in microwave for 6 to 7
minutes.
Top with
some
Mozzarella
cheese.
Cook
until cheese is melted. Let stand 8 minutes, then serve.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Debone and shred turkey. Mix with soups and broth.
Cook down 4 hours at 250°.

title: uncle bill's candy(serves 1 or 2)
directions: Cook this in a microwave-safe container which holds 3 times the amount of ingredients or it will boil over.

title: sparkling fruit mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin for at least 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Gently stir in cold ginger ale.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Remove from refrigerator and stir for 15 seconds. Stir in grapes and oranges.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
(If using plastic mold, spray mold with nonstick cooking spray for easy unmolding.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill at least one hour or more before serving.

title: anisa's chicken nuggets
directions: Shake coating mix in large plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake.
Fry chicken in pan or deep fryer (making sure oil covers pieces well) for 5 minutes or until golden and crispy.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sift together 3/4 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt. Melt butter and chocolate together; mix with milk and vanilla. Stir into flour mixture.
Add broken nuts and blend thoroughly. Pour into well-greased cake dish.

title: bananas hawaiian
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel bananas and quarter each banana by cutting first lengthwise and then in half.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Combine brown sugar with liquids and spices; heat. Pour over bananas.
Spread with coconut and dot with butter. Sprinkle with rum flavoring or rum.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until bananas are tender.
Serve over vanilla ice cream.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Coat a skillet with cooking spray, place over medium heat until hot.
Add next 4 ingredients; cook until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain in a colander, pat dry with paper towels and set aside.

title: coconut chew cookies
directions: Beat 3/4 cup butter at medium speed with mixer until creamy. Gradually add 3/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour, beating well.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar to taste.
Chill in "icebox."
Divide lettuce between salad bowls.
Place onions around lettuce, then add eggs and crumbled bacon.

title: apple crisp
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Lightly grease 8-inch round pan with butter.
Peel 4 medium sized apples; slice thin.
Place around bottom of pan.
Mix the first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Put mixture on apples.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: damson preserves
directions: To the damsons, add water and sugar.
Boil together for 25 minutes.
Remove all seeds possible.
Let preserves set overnight. Put in jars and seal with paraffin wax.
Makes 5 pints.

title: three bean salad(makes 6 cups)
directions: Rinse and drain kidney beans.
Combine with other beans.
Add onion, celery, sugar, salt, pepper, oil and vinegar.
Refrigerate 24 hours, stirring several times.
To serve, drain off marinade and pour into lettuce lined bowl.

title: pecan griddle cakes
directions: Combine flour, pecans, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat together applesauce, milk, eggs and margarine.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Use 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Cook on greased nonstick griddle over medium-high heat, turning once. Makes 14 pancakes.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Cook flour, milk and salt until thick.
Cool.
Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and beat 10 minutes.

title: vegetable and fruit dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 pint.
Also makes a good slaw dressing.

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: Mix pineapple and cranberry sauce in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Take off heat and stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in ginger ale. Pour into a lightly greased 1-quart mold dish.
Chill until set.

title: choc-oat chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars and when creamy, add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt mixture.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet for 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocado and mix with cream cheese until smooth.
Mix in other ingredients as desired.
Refrigerate.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Mix salt with meal and slowly pour meal into boiling water until mixture begins to thicken.
When corn mush is thick, pour in dish and chill until well set.
Slice to fry or bake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In saucepan, heat until blended the soup, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add shrimp, celery, onion and unflavored gelatin; mix well.
Pour into medium size bowl and refrigerate until firm. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: puppy chow
directions: In microwave melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter, stirring frequently until smooth.
Takes a couple of minutes, depending on heat level used.
In large bowl pour mixture over Crispix and mix well.
Put confectioners sugar in a brown bag; pour in Crispix mixture and shake well (after closing the bag!).
If chocolate mixture is not coated well, add more confectioners sugar and shake again

title: arroz con pollo (yellow rice and chicken)
directions: Fry chicken in 3 ounces olive oil, until brown.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, saute onion, garlic and green pepper in 3 ounces olive oil.
Add tomato and simmer until soft.
Add water, flavoring packet, bay leaf and salt; stir well.
Add chicken and bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Bring to a boil again, add rice and return to a boil.
Stir once, cover tightly and simmer on low heat, 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not remove cover.
When done, garnish with peas and pimientos.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, brown sugar, cream, butter or margarine and vanilla over low heat in nonstick pan until it comes to soft-ball stage. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter; stir thoroughly.
Add walnuts and marshmallow cream to mixture; pour into buttered platter.
When cooled, scatter chocolate chips over the top.

title: pie crust, cholesterol free, pan mix
directions: Mix
together
the
milk
and the corn oil and put in a 9-inch pie
pan.
Add
the sugar and salt; mix well.
Add the flour to the mixture in the pie pan and stir with fork.
Press dough into shape of pan.
Add any desired filling and bake.

title: extra special salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as stated on box.
When almost jelled, add pineapple and nuts.
Let set until congealed.
Combine cream cheese and Dream Whip; spread over Jell-O.
Cook remaining ingredients until slightly thickened.
Cool.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with a few nuts.

title: spicy cheese bread(bread machine recipe)
directions: Note:
Use 1 teaspoon quick rise yeast; 1 1/2 teaspoons if using active dry yeast.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Combine dry jello, boiling water, pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish or other bowl.
Refrigerate until set. Combine remaining ingredients and spread over jelled salad.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix together and press into a 13 x 9 inch dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: italian chicken
directions: Skin chicken and place meaty-side down in a 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 spaghetti sauce and 1/2 Parmesan cheese over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Pour remaining sauce and cheese over chicken.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter until it is the consistency of peas.
Add buttermilk, raisins and caraway seed and stir until combined.
Gather into a ball.
Knead on a lightly floured surface for 1 minute.
Roll into a ball, pat down and shape into one round, flat loaf.
Brush with butter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
With sharp knife, cut large crosses deep into dough.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: shrimp new orleans
directions: Several hours before preparing the dish for serving, wash the shrimp in 6 changes of fresh water.
Allow the shrimp to completely drain in a colander in the refrigerator until cooking time.
At cooking time, combine in a saucepan the butter, lots of black pepper, garlic salt, lemon juice and the crab boil.
Set aside.
Place the unpeeled shrimp in a flat 3-quart baking dish. Bring the butter sauce to a boil; pour over the shrimp. Immediately put the shrimp under a hot broiler.
Allow shrimp to turn pink on one side, then turn shrimp over to broil until pink on the other side.
Turn oven off; allow shrimp to remain in hot oven 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot in bowls with hot French bread. Serves 3 to 4.

title: family swiss steak
directions: With mallet, pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 6 pieces.
In 9-inch pie pan, stir together flour, parsley, thyme and pepper.
Coat steak with flour mixture.

title: bundt vegetable bread
directions: Melt oleo in pan and saute vegetables.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into Bundt pan (it will be lumpy).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Saute chicken in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Stir flour into skillet drippings.
Add 1 cup chicken broth and the light cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until sauce thickens.
Stir in the Dijon mustard.
Add chicken; heat over low to medium heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole; arrange cut broccoli.
Place chicken on top and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, pepper and curry.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 8.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill for an hour or so.
Form into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with toothpicks.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda, spices and salt.
Set aside. In a separate bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, mayonnaise and pineapple; gradually beat in dry ingredients until well mixed. Stir in with a spoon carrots and walnuts.
Turn into 2 greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, eggs and pecans together.
This will be thick.
Spread or pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been well-greased, then combine cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar. Beat until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell for 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Cut 6 slices of cheese into pieces and set aside.
In large skillet, brown meat.
Pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, onion and bouillon; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs, flour and cheese pieces.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add dates and stir well.
Return to burner and cook without stirring until mixture forms a soft ball (238°).
Remove from fire and beat until mixture will drop from a spoon into a great mass.
Add nuts. Pour into a 10-inch square pan.
When cool enough, cut into squares.
(Does not do well in damp weather.)

title: monte cristo sandwich
directions: To assemble sandwiches, lay out 4 slices of bread.
Cover with turkey and Cheddar.
Add another layer of bread.
Cover that with Provolone and ham.
Top with remaining bread.
Beat eggs with flour, salt, white pepper and milk.
Dip sandwich in batter and deep fry at 390°, browning on both sides.
Keep warm until all four are fried.
To serve, cut in quarters; sprinkle with a little powdered sugar, if desired, and side with some jam for dipping. Serves 4 to 6.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onion.
Combine with 3/4 cup sugar and mix well.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling and pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Add milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours. Top with pie filling.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put apples into large mixing bowl.
Break eggs over this.
Add oil, sugar, spices, salt and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: southwest taco pie
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onions, drain.
Add taco seasoning. Set aside.
In bowl, mix refried beans with 4 ounces taco sauce. Put meat mixture in pie crust.
Top with refried bean mixture. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Top with shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes.
Use additional taco sauce, if desired.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour in greased casserole dish (use oleo).
Top with grated cheese and broken Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve with ham.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne in 4 to 6 quarts salted water (1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon oil), uncovered, for about 12 minutes.

title: tasty cabbage and tomatoes
directions: Heat bacon drippings in a heavy skillet; add onion and green pepper and saute until tender.
Add tomatoes; cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Mix and cook in a double boiler for about 1 hour. Serve over hot baked dessert.

title: crescent roll-ups
directions: Pop open crescent roll can. Roll out each square dough section. Spread cheese over entire square. Layer spinach leaves over cheese. Place turkey over spinach. Roll each square up from corner to corner. Cut each roll-up into 1-inch pieces. Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or follow baking directions according to crescent packaging.

title: maria's cranberry salad
directions: Using a food processor, chop cranberries and oranges. Meanwhile, dissolve sugar and Jell-O with hot water. Add ice cubes. Stir to thicken.
Add cranberries, oranges, celery and nuts. Stir and chill well.

title: tiramisu
directions: Note:
This recipe has been handed down for 6 generations and has always been a favorite.
Rhubarb may be substituted for the apples.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, bring water and bouillon cube to a boil.
Add broccoli and carrot.
Cook according to broccoli directions. Remove from heat.
Do not drain.
In separate pan, melt butter and slowly stir in flour.
Continue stirring while gradually adding milk.
Stir in cubed cheese, soup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add the broccoli mixture to the white sauce mixture and cook over medium heat until soup is thick.
Stir to keep from sticking.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine buttermilk, soda, salt and vanilla; add to the sugar mixture alternately with flour, mixing after each addition.
Fold in the apples and pecans.
Pour into muffin papers in muffin pan. Combine sugar and melted butter; sprinkle on top of each muffin. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean. Yields about 15 muffins.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix
first
three ingredients in blender.
(Add milk if too thick.) Add shrimp and serve with crackers.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat the eggs with sugar.
Blend in cream cheese.
Add vanilla and almond flavorings and salt; beat well, then spoon in sour cream and blend.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Move from heat. Add other ingredients.
Add oatmeal last.
Drop on foil and cool.

title: no cook peach pie
directions: Place half the peaches into the chocolate pie crust.
In a 1-quart bowl, prepare the pudding with a cup of milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Fold whipped cream (save a bit for the top) and lemon extract into pudding and spoon into the shell.
Top with the rest of the peaches and the cream.
Refrigerate.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, flavoring, salt, oil and warm potatoes mashed into yeast mixture.
Put 1/4 cup warm water into a large cup with yeast.
Let rise.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Let rise like yeast rolls.
Roll and cut doughnuts; fry in deep oil.

title: kale soup
directions: Combine potatoes, linguica, beans and onion, Cover with water. Cook until potatoes are tender. Add kale.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Spray heavy cast-iron pan or electric skillet with oil.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Toothpick should be moist when tested for doneness.

title: corn with basil
directions: Prepare corn as needed. Cut enough kernels from corn to measure 3 cups. Cook and stir corn, onion, celery and garlic in butter in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until onion is tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook until corn is tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Yields 8 servings. Has 95 calories per serving.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1 cup juice.
Dissolve Jell-O; add 7-Up, crushed pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: easy chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine meat, ketchup, water, chili powder, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 45 minutes, making sure to crumble meat into small pieces as it cooks.
Add partially drained beans and simmer about 15 minutes longer.
If desired, serve with topping of grated cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in a greased 9x5x3 inch loaf pan.
Round top slightly.
Bake at 325 degrees for 75 minutes.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Set waffle iron on medium heat.
Drop from teaspoon and bake 1 1/2 minutes.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting when cooled. Great summer treat. Don't need to use oven.

title: zero salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with a tight fitting lid. Shake well.
Herbs of your choice can be added.
No calories.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and flour.
Mix in raisins and then nuts. Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: In ungreased
8 x 8-inch pan combine well flour, sugar, cocoa, baking
soda, baking powder and salt.
Makes 3 holes in mixture; pour
oil into one, vanilla in another and vinegar in the third. Add
water
and mix well.
Baked in preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter in pan.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, mixing gently.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart dish or pan.
Dot with remaining butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green summer pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick pie shell and bake 15 minutes. Saute onions.
Add spinach.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl. Add onions and spinach.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: hammed up eggs
directions: Beat eggs.
Add ham, onion, pepper and water.
Mix.
Heat butter in 9-inch skillet.
Cook, covered, over low heat until firm, about 15 minutes.
Cut into quarters.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 6 tablespoons juice and mix with flour, sugar and margarine.
Toss cheese with pineapple.
Pour juice, flour and margarine mixture over pineapple and cheese mixture. Sprinkle crackers over that and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: goulash
directions: Place macaroni in boiling water.
Cover and let set.
Saute ground beef and onion together in large saucepan.
Drain.
Drain macaroni.
Add to meat mixture along with remaining ingredients. Add 1/2 cup of water.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Beat eggs separately and mix all together.
Makes 2 pies.

title: meat loaf in a potato ring
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 cup tomato sauce with mushrooms, bread crumbs, egg, salt and garlic.
Shape into a 7-inch round loaf in a deep 9-inch pie plate.
Overlap potatoes in a ring around loaf; sprinkle with onions.
Combine remaining tomato sauce, gravy mix and water.
Pour over meat and potatoes.
Bake at 375°
for 1 hour.
Cover with foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Spoon off fat if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: gourmet pea salad
directions: Thaw and drain peas.
Add onion, celery and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add bacon and cashews.
Mix and serve.
(May be presented on a bed of lettuce, if desired.)

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Halve tomatoes; spread with thin layer of Blue cheese. Sprinkle each lightly with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Top with fine dry bread crumbs mixed with the basil or oregano and put butter bits on top.
Broil the tomatoes 3 inches from heat for about 6 minutes or until tomatoes are brown and hot.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Pour apple juice and gelatin in a saucepan.
Allow to soften for several minutes.
In the blender, finely chop blueberries, one cup at a time.
Add lemon juice, spices and 2 cups chopped berries to gelatin.
Heat over medium-low heat until gelatin is dissolved. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining berries and mix well.
Pour into jars or plastic containers.
Store in the refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add salt, soda, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for eight hours or overnight.

title: puppy chow(for boys and girls, little or big ones)
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in a saucepan, stirring constantly.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl and mix well.
Place coated cereal in a large paper bag.
Add confectioners sugar and shake until well coated.
Makes 10 cups.

title: cucumber freeze pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, pepper and onion together.
Sprinkle with salt over top.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain off.
Add sugar, celery seed and vinegar.
Chill 3 days.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute bell pepper and onion in a little oleo. Brown ground meat.
Mix all ingredients together; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Chill one hour or until serving time.
Yields 6 servings.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Melt and pour 1 stick margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place all chicken on top of butter.
Spread
cream of chicken soup, then spread cream of celery soup.
Pour milk over mixture. Pour broth over mixture.
Put stuffing mix on top. Melt remaining stick of margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bake rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixing bowl, combine rice, milk, raisins, sugar, vanilla, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish coated with nonstick spray.
Bake 30 minutes.
Stir and bake 30 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press meat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, onion and green pepper on top of meat.
Pour soup over onion and pepper.
Cover top with rows of Tater Tots.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Cover with wine.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soups and onion soup mix and cover chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: janet's blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine, baking powder and salt as you would for pie crust.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for crumbs on top of cake.
Lightly flour berries and add to dry mixture.
Beat eggs well.
Combine with 3/4 cup milk.
Add eggs and milk to dry mixture, folding in.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan (or two 9-inch pans).
Sprinkle with cinnamon and reserved crumb mixture. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Press firmly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl mix sugar, eggs, soft oleo and vanilla or almond; beat until very fluffy.

title: russian chicken
directions: Flour chicken on both sides.
Put in a large baking dish. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Heat Russian dressing and apricot preserves in saucepan.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: mock toffee
directions: Put in pot. Slow boil for 3 minutes. Spoon on cinnamon crisp crackers and nuts.
Bake about 8 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and sour cream together.
Add mandarin oranges, drained.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator until completely chilled.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Serve hot with crackers or small chunks of sourdough bread.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Sugar and flour measured to each 4 cups of berries.
Mix together and put over lattice work crust.
Cut 2 tablespoons butter into pieces and scatter on top of berry mixture before adding top lattice work crust.
Cook at 350° until crust is golden brown on top.

title: cookie pie crust
directions: Mix and pat into greased pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Use as crust for cream pies.

title: dreamer's delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until very stiff. Gradually add sugar, mixing well. Add dates and nuts and mix well. Drop on wax paper. Bake 10 minutes.

title: lemon fluffy
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add the sugar and lemon juice.

Mix well and chill until slightly congealed. Beat the chilled milk at high speed until very fluffy, adding the salt while beating. Slowly fold the milk into the slightly congealed gelatin until well mixed. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafers. Turn the gelatin mixture into the pan over the wafer crumbs and chill thoroughly.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine beaten eggs, bread crumbs, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Brown ground chuck.
Drain. Stir ground chuck into mixture.
On waxed paper, pat meat into 12 x 10-inch.
Arrange ham on top of meat and sprinkle shredded Mozzarella
cheese.
Roll up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from oven and top with cheese halves.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip softies
directions: Mix all ingredients for one minute.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: polish style sauerkraut
directions: Empty juice from jar.
Put kraut into saucepan and add 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring to a boil and cook 15 minutes.
(This takes out excess sourness.)
Drain well.
Then add 3/4 cup water and simmer slowly.
Meantime, fry onion in some bacon grease or butter until lightly brown.
Add to kraut and mushroom steak sauce.
Pepper to taste.
Stir well and simmer 10 minutes.
If still too sour, add 1 or 2 tablespoons of brown sugar.
Mix well.
Taste again.
Repeat brown sugar, if necessary.
Serves 6.

title: mud pie
directions: Now for the good stuff.
Mix powdered sugar with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Fold in softened cream cheese.
Mix and spread over crust. Make pudding, then spread over the good stuff (cream cheese, etc.).
Spread remaining Cool Whip over the top.
Chill.
Serve.

title: pasta sauce with fresh herbs
directions: In a small saucepan, heat olive oil over low heat.
When oil is hot, but not smoking, remove pan from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Toss with prepared pasta.
Sprinkle with fresh Parmesan cheese and serve at once.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Mix all of the ingredients until well blended.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place chicken breasts, side by side, and cover with the blended ingredients.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and continue to bake an additional 20 minutes until tender.

title: white sauce(for bbq chicken)
directions: Beef stock: If regular beef stock is not available, dissolve 16 beef bouillon cubes in 4 quarts of warm water.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain off fruit juices and combine all ingredients.
Serve chilled.
Other options include 2 to 3 diced apples, mini marshmallows, shredded coconut and whipped cream or yogurt as a sauce.

title: heavenly cheese pie
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve syrup.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in reserved pineapple syrup.
Add pudding mix and salt.
Beat at low speed until well blended, about 2 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce(for large amount)
directions: Cook 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
flour and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to flour-sugar mixture.
Stir
in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 minutes or until center is firm in 325° oven.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add one egg at a time and beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately and mix well.
Add coconut flavoring and coconut.
Bake in a stem pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: In a large saucepan add oil.
Brown meat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until transparent.
Add sugar and mushrooms; cook only until blended.
Add sour cream mixed with tomato paste just before serving.
Cook only until blended and hot.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: no crust lemon coconut cream pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 1 cup ice cubes, stirring until jello thickens.
Slowly sprinkle in dry nonfat milk.
Slowly add and whip until fluffy.
Then add topping, mixing slowly until smooth.
Blend in coconut.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: spicy sausage-bean soup
directions: Brown sausage in a large Dutch oven, stirring to crumble meat. Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in next 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add green pepper and potatoes.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 11 cups.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Precook bacon slightly to remove fat.
Wrap each chicken breast with bacon.
Cover bottom of 8 x 11-inch casserole with dried beef.
Top with chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
With wet hands, roll into small balls.
Freeze separated on a cookie sheet for 1 hour.
Put in a Baggie.
Bake frozen for 25 minutes at 375°.
Makes 80 balls.

title: pinto beans
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours.

title: red bean chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef until it loses red color, but does not brown.
Add onion, garlic and chili powder; cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes which have been mashed, red beans, salt, sugar, vinegar and water. Simmer 30 minutes or longer.
This can be a quick meal, but flavor improves if there is time to cook the chili slowly for an hour or so.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk until soft.
Beat eggs until light; add vanilla, sugar, salt, nutmeg and raisins. Mix with bread mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350° until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: percolator punch
directions: Dissolve brown sugar in pineapple juice, cranberry juice and water.
Pour into coffeepot.
Place lemon slices, cinnamon sticks and cloves in the basket of coffeepot.
Perk until good and hot.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine slightly beaten eggs with sugar and salt.
Slowly stir in slightly cooled milk and vanilla.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Fill a 9-inch cake pan with water and place casserole dish in the water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
The custard is done when knife comes out clean.
Check in middle.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Mix together (except cream); add enough cream to moisten. Form into roll; wrap in waxed paper and chill in the fridge for several hours.
Cut in slices and serve with whipped cream.

title: party wieners
directions: Cut wieners in 1-inch lengths.
Mix ingredients in a crock-pot.
Put in wieners.
Cook on low heat until thoroughly hot, about 3 to 4 hours.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: south carolina chews
directions: Cream margarine.
Add brown sugar and continue to cream.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture; mix until crumbly.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat cake mix (dry), water and eggs in large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls, 3-inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Insert wooden sticks 1 1/2-inches into edge of dough.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes or until puffed and almost no indentation remains when touched.
Cool on wire rack. Frost and decorate.
Makes 20 to 24 cookies.

title: sugar free banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter; press into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 375 degrees.
Cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.
After mixed well, roll into 1-inch balls.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Chop and mix together all ingredients, except pie filling. After mixing, pour peach pie filling over and mix again.
Let sit about 1 hour in refrigerator for fruit to blend before serving.

title: cranberry tea
directions: In a 3 qt. saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, over medium heat.
Boil for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove cinnamon and cloves.
To serve, mix 1 c. concentrate and 2 c. water, heat through.
Store 1 c. concentrate in a covered container in the fridge.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly mix 1/4 cup of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
In a 9-inch pie plate, shape firmly into ring.
Bake for about 1 hour or until done.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Heat pineapple juice (about 9 ounces) in a double boiler.
Mix together eggs, flour and sugar.
Add to hot juice and cook until thickened.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, add Cool Whip (more or less than 1 cup, according to taste).

title: great french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, fork whip eggs, milk, nutmeg and vanilla extract until blended and frothy.
Dip each bread slice into egg mixture, coating bread completely.
In a shallow bowl, dip each slice of bread into crushed corn flakes, covering bread completely.
Pan-fry coated bread slices in melted margarine or butter until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with maple syrup or powdered sugar.

title: delicious hors d'oeuvres("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Mix the three ingredients together well.
Make small ball shapes about the size of marbles or roll in long rolls about 1/2-inch in diameter and slice and bake as needed at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients; pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: curried pear and parsnip soup
directions: Bring chicken stock, parsnips, onion, curry powder, pepper and bay leaf to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered and stirring often, for about 30 minutes or until vegetables are very tender. Discard bay leaf. Transfer in batches to blender or food processor; puree until smooth. Return to pan; add milk and heat thoroughly.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in hot fat.
Pour water and coffee over roast.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a brisk boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes.
Add tomatoes, onion and carrots.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: best ever blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In 8-inch square baking dish, mix blueberries, 3 Tbsp. sugar and orange juice. Set aside. In small bowl, thoroughly mix flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In a medium bowl, cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla extract. Gradually add flour mixture, stirring just until ingredients are combined. Drop batter by rounded tablespoons over blueberry mixture. Try to cover as much of filling as possible. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until top is golden brown and filling is bubbly.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla wafers, coconut and pecans.
Grease a tube pan well.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour at 300°.
Loosen cake after removing from oven.
Let stand about 20 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and Italian sausage; set aside.
Melt butter; add celery and olives.
Cook on medium-high for about 20 minutes. Add onion and garlic and cook about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and bay leaf; cook about 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, ground beef, Italian sausage and all spices, except chives and parsley.
Cook for a while so spices go through sauce.

title: broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Break up broccoli and cauliflower and mix with onions.
In bowl beat mayonnaise, sugar, vegetable oil and vinegar together. Combine with broccoli, cauliflower and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, and sugar until well blended.
Slowly add flour.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Batter will be very thick. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour batter into it.
Bake at 350 for one hour or until a cake tester inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: frozen punch
directions: Put in freezer and freeze until just before you are ready to serve.
An hour or two before serving time, remove from freezer. Then stir until mixture becomes a mush.
Serve.

title: frosting bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix 1 cup of the frosting, the eggs, flour, baking powder and nuts in a medium-size bowl.
Cover and reserve remaining frosting.
Spread frosting mixture in a pan.
Bake until wooden toothpick when inserted in the center, comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Spread with reserved frosting.
Cut into bars (about 2 x 1 1/2-inches).

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown and drain meat.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning; simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough and press on bottom sides of ungreased pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Cover crust with meat mixture and top with cheese.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients and garnish with sour cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo with lid on pan 2 minutes.
Then uncover and cook, without stirring, until hard boil stage or spins thread.
Add raw peanuts and margarine.
Stir until peanuts are roasted, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Beat quickly, stirring in soda thoroughly.
Spread on buttered tin.
