When cooled, break into pieces.

title: old fashioned peach cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend at low speed about 1 minute, until completely moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with topping.

title: unbelievable lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In blender container combine all ingred. except coconut.
Blend on low 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near edge comes out clean. Cool slightly; serve warm or cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: crushed pineapple zucchini
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.
Place in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: outrageous banana bread
directions: Cream butter and honey.
Add eggs, yogurt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add cereal.
Mash bananas in a separate bowl.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, deviled ham, scallions and chilies; mix well.
Shape mixture into a ball. Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill.
Remove from refrigerator to soften slightly before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 (2 cup) cheese ball.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; skin and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and drain.
Melt oleo; saute celery, bell pepper and onion until almost tender.
Add soup, tomato juice, catsup and mushrooms.
Alternate in layers.
Bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese omelet
directions: Add 1/2 tablespoon butter, salt, cayenne and cheese to eggs. In top pan of chafing dish, set in water jacket.
Put remaining butter.
Add egg mixture.
Cook, without stirring, until firm. Roll and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: frothy fruit shake
directions: Place fruit and salt in a blender and puree.
Combine puree with 1/2 cup of finely crushed ice or add ice cubes to the puree in the blender and blend until the cubes are crushed.
Use your imagination and use any combination of fruit.
Makes 2 cup servings.
Contains 105 cal/serving and 0 sat. fat.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream together first five ingredients.
Add next four ingredients.
Mix together.
Add apples last.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch greased tin at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: cream cheese patties
directions: Mix dry ingredients separately in blender; put in bowl.
Then mix cheese and eggs in blender.
Add other ingredients.
Fry in patties over low heat.
These burn easily.
Use tomato soup or sauce over top.

title: one-dish chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend soup, milk, salt, pepper and mayonnaise in bowl. Combine chicken, onion, peas, bell pepper and rice in a large bowl; mix gently. Gently fold soup mixture into chicken mixture to combine. Fold in half of the cheese. Spray a medium casserole dish with cooking spray. Spoon in chicken mixture. Sprinkle top of casserole with remaining cheese. Bake until top is golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: monterey casserole
directions: Parboil sliced zucchini.
Slit chilies and remove seeds.
Cut half of the cheese in strips.
In a well-buttered (9 x 13 x 2-inch) casserole, place rice, a layer of open chilies, a layer of cheese, zucchini and tomatoes, chopped bell pepper and chopped green onion.
Mix the sour cream and spices and pour over the vegetables.
Grate the rest of the cheese and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheaters lasagna
directions: Brown meat and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Stir together sour cream, cream cheese and onions.
Use mixer.
Layer noodles and cream mixture, meat sauce. Then sprinkle with cheese.
It makes 2 layers.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: chow mein candy
directions: Melt both types morsels over low heat; remove from heat and add noodles and nuts.
Stir until all coated.
Spoon onto wax paper; let sit.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Mix crumbs with 1 tablespoon sugar and butter.
Put 1/2 crumbs in Pyrex baking dish; press to form a crust.
Chill the milk in bowl in the freezer until crystals form; whip until stiff.
Crush cranberry sauce with a fork in a mixing bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and almond flavoring.
Fold whipped milk into cranberries. Pour over crumbs.
Add additional crumbs.

title: pecan fudge sheetcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 15 1/2 X 10 1/2 in. pan. Prepare cake following package directions for basic recipe.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until tooth pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oven meat balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix beef, spices, onion, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix tomato soup and water; pour over meat balls.
Cover dish; bake for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is thoroughly cooked.
Makes about 25 meat balls.

title: peek-a-boos
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, then flour, a little at a time, mixing well. Spread 3/4 of the dough up sides of cookie sheet.

title: mystery cherry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar and baking powder. Beat in vanilla.
Fold in Ritz crackers and pecans.
Spread in buttered 10-inch pie pan and press against sides to form shell. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly brown.
When cool, fill with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: honey strawberry nog
directions: In blender or bowl, combine milk, honey, strawberries and vanilla.
Whirl in blender or beat.
Serve in tall glasses.
Top with scoops of vanilla or strawberry ice cream.

title: jumbo oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter until smooth. Add sugars, eggs, milk and vanilla. Blend well. Sift together the flour, soda and cinnamon. Stir into creamed mixture.
Add oats and raisins. Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package (but no butter).
Add pepper, onions, olives and artichokes.
Add mayonnaise to marinade.
Add curry to taste.
Toss all together.
Chill overnight.
Great salad for potluck or buffets.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Place grated cucumbers between paper towels and press as much of the liquid out as possible.
Then combine cucumbers with remaining ingredients and blend well.

title: coconut delight
directions: Combine flour, butter, sugar and nuts, then press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
This will be the crust.
Let cool.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ice cubes, in a blender. Cover and blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes, 1 to 2 at a time, and continue blending until ice is completely crushed.
Serve immediately.

title: dads shortbread
directions: Rub in butter and flour until it resembles bread crumbs. Mix in sugar. Knead until mixed thoroughly. Mixture will be dry. Roll out to about 1 inch thick to desired shape. Prick with a fork. Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage, drain and cool.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and mustard.
Cube bread and stir into milk mixture.
Then add cheese and sausage.
Bake in 8 x 10-inch dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef pilaf
directions: Brown meat.
Put onion, pepper, garlic, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper in blender.
Chop for 3 seconds.
Mix rice, meat and other ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Sprinkle garlic salt over top, if desired.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Pat shrimp dry with paper towels; set aside.
Melt butter in a wide frying pan over medium heat.
Stir in green onion, oil, garlic, lemon juice and salt.
Cook until bubbly.
Add shrimp to pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp turn pink (4 to 5 minutes).
Stir in parsley, lemon peel and hot pepper sauce. Great!

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and cook with onion, bouillon and salt until tender.
Cook, uncovered, and let some water boil off. Add butter and milk.
Serve topped with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in rest of flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal. Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.

title: watermelon bombe
directions: Line large bowl with Saran Wrap. Soften the sherbet and the ice cream. Press the lime sherbet into the bowl, covering the bottom and sides up to the rim. Freeze until very firm. Repeat with vanilla ice cream. Mix some chocolate sprinkles into the softened raspberry sherbet and fill the middle of the bowl with this mixture. Freeze until very firm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in a slightly greased baking dish. Combine mayonnaise, chicken soup and sherry.
Pour over chicken. Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Spread apples in 24 ounce casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Microwave, uncovered, on High until apples are tender, 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Boil mixture for 3 minutes.
Toss over pecans.
Pour out on foil to cool.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 cups.

title: cream of broccoli soup(quick)
directions: Wash and chop broccoli.
Place into 2 cups boiling water; cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove broccoli with a slotted spoon, leaving cooking water in saucepan.
Add milk to bring back to 2 cups liquid.
Whisk in 1 can cream of chicken soup (prefer Campbell's). Do not boil, just heat as you add 1 cup cubed or shredded cheese. (I like a combination of Monterey Jack and sharp American.)
When smooth and cheese has melted, return broccoli to soup and bring up to warmth wanted, but do not boil.
Milk may be added to thin soup, if needed.
I sometimes add chopped leftover chicken.

title: dainty salad
directions: Whip cream.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; let cool.
When almost congealed, whip until very light and frothy.
Add celery, cheese and pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill thoroughly.

title: hawaiian baked pork
directions: Put pineapple in large buttered baking dish.
Place pared and sliced sweet potatoes over pineapple and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Salt and pepper the pork and place on top of the sweet potatoes.
Place bacon strips on top of the pork.

title: lisa's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, pumpkin and water together.
Add all the dry ingredients and stir well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Put into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Finely	chop zucchini, onion, carrot, leeks and celery. Saute vegetables	in
oil.
Add
garlic,	pepper, oregano and parsley. Set
aside.
Blend	mayonnaise, Parmesan and cottage cheese. Layer
cooked lasagna noodles with vegetable mixture, then mayonnaise-cheese mixture.	Bake 35 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients at once.
Stir until all blended. Serve with all your favorite vegetables.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Turn into small cakes.
Dip into mixture of half flour and half corn meal.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Cook meat, onion and pepper in large skillet until meat is lightly browned and vegetables are tender. Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives and all remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Turn into greased baking dish.

title: parsley-parmesan baked chicken
directions: Pour salad dressing in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Add chicken and coat well.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours.
Occasionally spoon dressing over chicken.
Drain; reserve dressing.
Combine egg and water in separate bowl.
In plastic bag (Ziploc), combine cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then shake in crumb mixture.
Return coated chicken to baking dish and spoon reserved dressing over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.

title: aunt wanda's play dough recipe
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until dough forms.
Break into pieces and add coloring.

title: mexican hush puppies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Stir in corn and next 3 ingredients (do not overmix batter).

Pour oil to depth of 2-inches into a small Dutch oven; heat to 375°. Carefully drop batter by rounded tablespoonfuls into oil, fry only a few at a time, 3 minutes or until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels.
Good with fish, beans or anything.
Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend the peanut butter and powdered sugar together and sprinkle 2/3 of it into baked pie shell.
Blend together the flour, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Add the milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir a little of the pudding mixture into 2 beaten egg yolks.
Combine and cook several minutes longer. Add the oleo and vanilla; pour the mixture into pie shell.
Pile meringue on top of pie, then sprinkle with remaining peanut butter mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or less until the color desired is obtained.

title: rice and beef casserole
directions: Brown the ingredients in the butter.
After this is brown, put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour 1 can beef consomme soup and 1 cup water.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Mix together pineapple and cream cheese.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add diced cherries.
Put in dish and add ground nuts on top.
Chill 1 hour.

title: sunday night noodles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook noodles to desired doneness; drain.
In a large bowl, mix the thawed spinach, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Stir in noodles.
Spoon the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan coated with nonstick spray.
In a small bowl, combine the melted butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over noodle mixture.
Bake covered for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and, with buttermilk, add to the dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix preceding ingredients (except corn) and cook slowly for 2 hours.
During last 30 minutes, add corn and finish cooking.

title: one hour dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; warm milk and pour over butter, stirring until creamy.
Add sugar; dissolve the yeast mixture in salt and flour.
The dough will be sticky.
Make 2-inch rolls. Place in a greased pan.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: In a saucepan, mix well all ingredients.
Bring slowly to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil briskly for 2 minutes.
(Boil 2 1/2 minutes on a rainy day.)
Cool to lukewarm. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until creamy and thick enough to spread.
Yields frosting for tops and sides of 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and water.
Add all ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.
Add ginger ale prior to serving.
May be used just as mixed fruit juice.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook in large pot and cook vegetables until desired tenderness.

title: peach cobbler(finger licking good)
directions: Make pie crust according to directions on box or make your own.
Roll and cut into strips.
Place a few crust strips in bottom of well-greased, 18 x 18-inch pan.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Melt margarine.
Next mix everything except potatoes together. Add potatoes; mix.
Let potatoes soak at least 1 hour.
Pour into pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 450° until potatoes are tender.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, cake mix, sour cream, Kahlua and vegetable oil.
Using electric mixer, beat at low speed to blend, then increase speed and beat for 3 to 5 minutes at medium-fast speed.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let simmer for 2 hours.
If any is leftover, freeze for another day.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Combine all soups; bring to a boil.
Add cream, shrimp and sherry.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can also use crabmeat or imitation crabmeat with the shrimp to make Seafood Bisque.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, water, sugar and jello in a saucepan and bring to boil for about 2 minutes.
Place strawberries in pie shell and pour jello mixture over
and top with Cool Whip once pie is cool.

title: english trifle("light refreshing dessert")
directions: Slice jelly roll and line the base of glass dessert bowl. Boil water and make Jell-O (strawberry-banana), using 1 3/4 cups of water in a small bowl. Set aside until it's cooled a little. Pour gently over cake. Cover up with plastic and refrigerate until set, about 2 hours.
Make a vanilla pudding.
Let cool some and then gently pour over Jell-O mixture.
Top
with sliced bananas. Cover with plastic and return to refrigerator.
When cold and set, top with whipped cream and decorate with fresh strawberries. Light and refreshing dessert.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend the pudding with the milk for 2 to 3 minutes on medium. Fold the Cool Whip in and continue to blend. Place crackers in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Alternate layers of crackers and pudding mix 3 times. Make sure to end with crackers. Put chocolate frosting in microwave for 30 seconds. While still warm, spread over top layer of crackers. Refrigerate until needed.

title: peppermint stick sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Constantly stirring with a wooden spoon, cook over medium heat until smooth. Place in an airtight container and refrigerate.
Serve chilled over ice cream or cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts.
May also add raisins, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Loaves freeze well.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Mix 1/4 cup of nuts with the other ingredients. Shape into a ball and coat it with the other 1/4 cup of nuts. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: children's play dough
directions: In medium boiler, add all ingredients, including desired color of food coloring.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick. Remove from heat and knead.
Let dough cool and place in airtight container.
Do not allow children to eat; this recipe is for play only.

title: boston cookies
directions: Cream
the butter.
Beat in sugar and egg.
Add 1/2 cup flour sifted with soda and salt.	Add cinnamon, nuts, raisins and
1/2 cup flour.	Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at	350°
for
approximately
10 minutes.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients into large mixing bowl and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Grease and flour the pan.

title: barbecued beef patties
directions: Moisten crumbs with milk.
Combine with meat, salt and pepper. Add chopped onion.
Shape into patties.
Place in an 8-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients to make barbecue sauce; pour around patties.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat 5 minutes.
Grease a tube or Bundt pan.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Turn cake upside down on plate to remove from pan.

title: potato fondant
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Knead with hands until smooth and creamy.
Shape into bonbons; dip in melted chocolate.
May be tinted with food coloring if desired.
May use rum, lemon, maple or any other extract instead of vanilla.
Mashed potatoes must be free of lumps to give candy smooth satiny texture.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over 2-pound brisket.
Place flat in pan.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours at 350°.
Baste occasionally while baking.

title: imitation crab cakes
directions: Cook fish until done and flake.
Crumble bread and combine with remaining ingredients.
Form into patties and fry in hot oil.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In a large
Teflon skillet, saute green onions, parsley and garlic in margarine until onions are soft.
Reduce heat to low; add shrimp, stirring constantly.
Cook 3 minutes and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer
more
minutes.
This can be served separately in a
bowl
or
over
cooked
rice.
It also makes a good appetizer
by placing equal amounts of shrimp and sauce in individual serving bowls.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put small amount of oil in pan.
Add ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook until beef is no longer pink.
Scoop out excess grease.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Serve over spaghetti.

title: no-fat salsa
directions: Cut vegetables into 1/2-inch or smaller size.
Combine all ingredients.
Put aside 1/2 cup mixture.
Put remaining ingredients into food processor or blender.
Using a pulsing (on-off) motion, process to desired texture.
If you do not have a food processor or blender, chop as fine as possible.
Add 1/2 cup mixture back into blended salsa and stir.
This will provide chunkier texture. Transfer to shallow serving dish.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Puree corn in processor.
Shred cheese.
Add all ingredients into processor and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is crusty and center has set.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Wash, seed, and core tomatoes. Chop into small cubes (so it makes roughly 1 to 1 1/2 cups). Dice onion into small cubes and add to tomatoes. You may add more than 1/4 c. onions if you desire a stronger onion flavor. Cut the lime in half and squeeze the juice from both halves into the tomato/onion mixture. Remove cilantro leaves from the stems; discard stems. Chop cilantro leaves and add to mixture. Stir and add salt (no more than 1 or 2 tsp.). Enjoy!

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, put shortening.
Add 1 cup boiling water to melt shortening, then add 1 cup cold water.
Add beaten eggs, salt, yeast and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Place a greased lid over bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: lazy man's meat balls
directions: Mix barbecue sauce and grape jelly in crock-pot.
Add meat balls to mixture.
Cover and cook about 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Delicious served over rice, with sauce.
Or as an appetizer with toothpicks.

title: souper rice supper
directions: Prepare a can of cream of mushroom soup.
Then add instant rice to boiling soup.
Stir in broccoli, American cheese (cut in pieces) and diced cooked Spam, ham, chicken or tuna, drained and flaked.
Stir, cover, remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Crush cornflakes to make 2 cups of crumbs.
Add garlic salt and pepper.
Select broiler-fryer.
Dip pieces in margarine; roll in crumb mixture.
Place pieces, skin side up and not touching, in a greased pan.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Don't turn.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread with orange glaze
directions: In large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture and stir well.
Pour batter into 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until bread tests done. Cool on racks.
Drizzle glaze over top.

title: banana applesauce nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease only the bottom of a loaf pan with shortening.
Mix sugar and oil in a bowl with a mixer.
Add the eggs.
Add the mashed bananas; mix well.
Stir in the other ingredients except the nuts and raisins.
Add them last.
Turn mixture into greased bottom (only) pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick for doneness (when pick comes out clean, it's done).
Let stand in the pan for 5 to 10 minutes.
Loosen sides with a knife and turn out onto a cooling rack.

title: joanne's hawaiian chicken
directions: Melt butter in shallow roasting pan.
Roll chicken pieces in butter until well coated.
Arrange the pieces in single layer in pan.
Reserve 2 slices of the pineapple for garnishing the platter.
Dice remaining slices.
Mix the pineapple juice with remaining ingredients.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add drained pineapple pieces.
Spoon one-half of the sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 30 to 45 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.
Baste chicken occasionally with remaining sauce.
Arrange chicken on hot platter.
Cut reserved pineapple slices in half. Twist each half to make an "S".
Place on chicken platter. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Place a layer of diced eggplant in casserole.
Top with layer of green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle on the soy grits.
Top with rest of eggplant, pepper and onion.
Add tomatoes.
Cover and bake 40 minutes in a moderate oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon jelly roll
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, heat ingredients and bring to boiling; stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute; set aside.
Cool to room temperature.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix together.
Make 2 large rolls or 3 small rolls.
Roll in extra crumbs.
Roll in aluminum foil, chill at least 2 hours. Overnight is better.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of the soup with beef, egg, crumbs, onion and seasonings.
Shape into 6 patties that are flat and quite thick. Brown patties in a small amount of oil in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Mix remaining soup, water and parsley.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: veggie cheese bake
directions: In casserole dish, layer zucchini, mushrooms, green pepper and onions.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Add cheese and bread crumbs. Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Equals lunch protein plus 1 ounce bread and 2 ounces milk.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and melted butter.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk and vanilla.
You may need to add more flour; dough should be soft.
If sticky, add some oil to hands when rolling.

title: melt-a-way chocolate pie
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add egg yolks individually to chocolate mix and beat each time.
Beat egg whites with salt to soft peaks.
Add vanilla; beat again.
Fold egg whites into chocolate mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.
Decorate with whipped cream and shaved chocolate curls.
Try a chocolate cookie crust sometime, too.

title: almond candy
directions: Mix marshmallows and nuts.
Melt almond bark in microwave for 3 minutes, or until smooth.
Mix with marshmallows and nuts; drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Store in tight containers.

title: garlic potatoes baked in foil
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; stir potatoes to coat. Wrap potatoes in two 12-inch square foil pouches, sealing all edges.
Grill over medium flame for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Lightly pound the chicken breasts to make them even thickness. Using a small pot with the chicken between plastic wrap works well.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls. Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping and fruit. Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Chill about 3 hours or freeze until firm.
Makes 8 servings. Garnish.
If you're counting calories, try Jell-O gelatin.

title: fried oysters
directions: Dip oysters in egg and dredge in cracker crumbs.
Place in a pan and chill for 2 hours.
Stir together ketchup, horseradish and hot sauce.
Pour oil to 1 inch depth in a Dutch oven and heat to 350 degrees.
Fry oysters in batches for 3-4 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on a paper towel and serve immediately with ketchup sauce.

title: the fish dish
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Clean fish and arrange in an 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer the fillet of sole over the haddock and scatter scallops over the top.
Sprinkle the lemon pepper and a dash of milk over the top.
Slice a 6 ounce package of Velveeta cheese and lay over the top of the fish.
Combine the topping as follows:
Crumble 1 1/2 rolls of Ritz crackers.
Add garlic, sage and parsley.
Toss together.
Melt butter and sprinkle over top until you have a crumb mixture.
Spread crumb topping over fish and bake for 40 minutes.
If crumb mixture starts to brown, put aluminum foil over the dish.
Enjoy!
May be served with vegetable rice pilaf, broccoli and Chardonnay.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Pour lemon extract over pecans and let stand overnight. Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time, mixing well.
Add fruit and raisins that have been dusted with about 1 Tbsp. flour.
Add pecans and stir with a spoon.
Grease and line a tube pan with wax paper.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 250 degrees for 2-1/2 to 3 hours.

title: pork chops and potato casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and water in a small bowl; blend well.
Alternate layers of potatoes and soup mixture in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Clean and cut up cauliflower and broccoli; steam for 15 minutes.
Put in 9 x 11-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix all together: cream of celery soup, milk and Cheddar cheese.
Stir in with vegetables.
Melt margarine, mix in with 1/2 cup Italian bread crumbs.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger
on
bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add sliced potatoes,
onions
and
peas.
Dilute soup with 1/2 cup water and spoon on top of casserole.
Cover with foil and bake in oven
for 1 hour or until potatoes and onions are tender.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Mix well and pour over enchiladas (I prefer flour tortillas). Top with grated cheese.
Makes approximately 2 dozen enchiladas.

title: peas and hash casserole
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger and onion in hot shortening, stirring to separate beef into small pieces.
Season with salt and pepper. Drain peas and reserve 1/2 of the liquid.
Add peas, reserved liquid and potatoes.
Heat over low temperature until vegetables are hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: charleston torte(aka huguenot torte)
directions: Beat whole eggs in electric mixer until very frothy and lemon colored.
Add other ingredients in above order.
Pour into two well-buttered baking pans, 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes for an 8 x 12-inch pan or for 30 to 35 minutes for a 9 x 13-inch pan, until crusty and brown.
Cut into 16 or 18 pieces and serve with crusty part on top.
Cover with whipped cream and a sprinkling of chopped nuts.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine all ingredients except beets and heat to boiling.
Add cooked, peeled beets and heat until heated through and ladle into sterilized fruit jars.
Seal with lids.
Makes 4 pints.

title: curried fruit
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and curry powder.
Drain fruit.
Place in casserole dish.
Spoon sugar mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Good with any meat dish.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, green pepper and onion.
Add ground beef and brown it.
Stir in soups and water.
Add the cooked spaghetti. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dave's chicken gumbo
directions: In large pot, saute onions and pepper in oil until tender. Stir in water, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes longer.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: barge rice
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve with chips as a dip.

title: patio beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Saute onion in bacon drippings. Combine in large casserole the beans, cheese, brown sugar and seasonings. Stir in crumbled bacon and onion.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: chicken, rice chutney salad
directions: Combine French dressing and mango.
Mix other ingredients. Add dressing and chill.
Garnish with cashews.

title: stuffed baked flounder
directions: Add beaten eggs to crabmeat; mix well.
Place 1 fillet in foil-lined pan.
Spread crabmeat on fillet.
Top with other fillet.
Add potatoes and onion.
Season with salt and pepper. Top with bacon strips.
Add about 1 cup water.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until potatoes are done and bacon crisp.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: lemon bread(breakfast)
directions: Combine milk, juice and thyme.
Bring to boil and cool.
Cream in large mixer bowl the butter.
Add sugar and beat well.
Then eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt) together.
Add alternately with milk mixture to the butter and sugar mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add the lemon rind and stir through well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Test with a wooden toothpick for doneness.
If desired, you can glaze it or just dust with powdered sugar.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar with water.
Add instant coffee and vanilla bean. Let cool (very important)!
Add vodka.
Store in an empty gallon milk jug in a cool, dark place for 3 weeks.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 375° or until done.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn into roasting size pan.
Mix sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in saucepan and cook gently on medium heat, stirring constantly.
When begins to boil, cook 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla (dissolved together) until mixture foams.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat.
Bake 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool and crumble into small pieces.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add cooled butter, chopped nuts, chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashion brown bread
directions: Boil for 2 minutes the Raisins, Water, and Shortening.
Cool. Add the remaining ingredients to the Raisin mixture and beat well. Place in 2 well-greased 11 - 13 oz. coffee cans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350.
